- Two! Three! - Two! Three!

270
00:11:28,768 --> 00:11:30,468
- Nice. - No!

271
00:11:30,898 --> 00:11:33,198
(I failed with the backflip.)

272
00:11:34,868 --> 00:11:37,068
(He attempted the backflip with confidence.)

273
00:11:38,208 --> 00:11:40,608
(He fell straight down.)

274
00:11:41,438 --> 00:11:43,678
- One more time? - One more time?

275
00:11:45,678 --> 00:11:47,878
(He gets back up on the diving board.)

276
00:11:48,248 --> 00:11:49,287
He's doing it again.

277
00:11:49,288 --> 00:11:50,648
(Amazed)

278
00:11:51,348 --> 00:11:53,158
- Like this with the knees. - Right.

279
00:11:55,118 --> 00:11:57,958
(Dex never gives up.)

280
00:11:58,528 --> 00:11:59,727
Okay?

281
00:11:59,728 --> 00:12:01,928
(He makes another attempt with the backflip dive.)

282
00:12:02,468 --> 00:12:03,697
Okay.

283
00:12:03,698 --> 00:12:05,368
(Let's do well this time.)

284
00:12:05,698 --> 00:12:06,868
- One! - Let's go!

285
00:12:07,338 --> 00:12:08,468
- Two! - Two!

286
00:12:09,068 --> 00:12:10,108
- Three! - Three!

287
00:12:21,418 --> 00:12:22,688
Oh, my gosh!

288
00:12:26,758 --> 00:12:29,988
(Diving without hesitation)

289
00:12:33,658 --> 00:12:36,327
(He manages to pull off the refreshing backflip as well.)

290
00:12:36,328 --> 00:12:38,068
(Amazed)

291
00:12:41,098 --> 00:12:44,567
(You're the best, Dex.)

292
00:12:44,568 --> 00:12:45,878
He seems to be having fun.

293
00:12:46,108 --> 00:12:47,578
He loves these activities.

294
00:12:49,148 --> 00:12:52,548
(He experienced the jungle of Bohol with his entire body.)

295
00:12:52,748 --> 00:12:53,848
This is fun.

296
00:12:53,948 --> 00:12:55,077
Aren't we really having fun?

297
00:12:55,078 --> 00:12:56,848
Yes, I'm having fun just by watching.

298
00:12:57,048 --> 00:12:58,887
It feels like real vacation.

299
00:12:58,888 --> 00:12:59,888
(It's time to go back after enjoying the jungle.)

300
00:13:00,158 --> 00:13:02,388
(Heave-ho)

301
00:13:02,988 --> 00:13:05,397
(Si Eon powers up the paddle board.)

302
00:13:05,398 --> 00:13:06,498
(I'm going first.)

303
00:13:07,628 --> 00:13:08,628
Jung Ah, what do you think of my speed?

304
00:13:08,629 --> 00:13:09,867
Your rowing got really fast.

305
00:13:09,868 --> 00:13:11,167
My speed...

306
00:13:11,168 --> 00:13:12,168
You're getting a workout.

307
00:13:12,538 --> 00:13:14,197
- I'm getting a lot of workout. - Right.

308
00:13:14,198 --> 00:13:15,338
I'll think about it when I'm trying to sleep.

309
00:13:17,268 --> 00:13:18,438
Here I go.

310
00:13:20,378 --> 00:13:22,677
(Meanwhile, Jun Myun looks completely knocked out.)

311
00:13:22,678 --> 00:13:25,448
(Spotting Jun Myun)

312
00:13:25,918 --> 00:13:28,688
(Suddenly, he moves toward Jun Myun.)

313
00:13:29,348 --> 00:13:31,648
(He starts fiddling with Jun Myun's board.)

314
00:13:33,558 --> 00:13:35,858
I'll pull you. We have to go all the way back.

315
00:13:36,758 --> 00:13:38,998
(Moved by Dex)

316
00:13:39,628 --> 00:13:42,227
- Jun Myun, isn't it tiring? - Yes.

317
00:13:42,228 --> 00:13:45,098
(Dex is the only one who understands Jun Myun.)

318
00:13:46,598 --> 00:13:50,538
(Just like the days when he rode his bike with Jun Myun on the back)

319
00:13:51,838 --> 00:13:54,808
(Even today, Dex leads the way to keep her safe.)

320
00:13:55,308 --> 00:13:57,848
(Just follow me.)

321
00:13:58,378 --> 00:14:00,977
(Thanks to him, she's smiling again.)

322
00:14:00,978 --> 00:14:02,017
Now...

323
00:14:02,018 --> 00:14:04,148
(Loboc River warmed up with their comradeship.)

324
00:14:05,218 --> 00:14:07,187
(Glancing)

325
00:14:07,188 --> 00:14:08,317
(Hye Yoon spots Jun Myun and Dex.)

326
00:14:08,318 --> 00:14:09,388
You caught up.

327
00:14:09,688 --> 00:14:11,787
Could you attach mine to your board too?

328
00:14:11,788 --> 00:14:13,598
- Could you attach mine too? - Come here.

329
00:14:15,098 --> 00:14:16,998
- There's something I want to do. - What?

330
00:14:17,868 --> 00:14:19,138
I want to advance while lying down.

331
00:14:20,838 --> 00:14:21,938
We're united.

332
00:14:22,108 --> 00:14:23,238
There's something I want to do.

333
00:14:23,568 --> 00:14:25,107
- You want to lie down... - Yes.

334
00:14:25,108 --> 00:14:26,138
and enjoy the ride?

335
00:14:27,138 --> 00:14:29,147
You want to make me work.

336
00:14:29,148 --> 00:14:30,177
Right.

337
00:14:30,178 --> 00:14:32,577
So you want to lie down comfortably during the ride?

338
00:14:32,578 --> 00:14:33,412
That's right.

339
00:14:33,678 --> 00:14:34,947
Where's the camera drone?

340
00:14:34,948 --> 00:14:36,687
You want to get a camera drone shot?

341
00:14:36,688 --> 00:14:37,747
That's right.

342
00:14:37,748 --> 00:14:40,388
Can you believe this cheeky girl?

343
00:14:40,488 --> 00:14:42,227
I checked the location of the camera drone.

344
00:14:42,252 --> 00:14:44,521
She wants to get a drone shot all to herself.

345
00:14:44,988 --> 00:14:45,997
To get a camera drone shot...

346
00:14:45,998 --> 00:14:48,328
Camera drone director, please film me.

347
00:14:49,674 --> 00:14:50,773
Look at her.

348
00:14:50,798 --> 00:14:52,538
(She just finds her cute.)

349
00:14:53,438 --> 00:14:56,208
(He starts rowing like crazy for the youngest.)

350
00:14:56,438 --> 00:14:59,708
(The camera drone also sets off.)

351
00:15:13,258 --> 00:15:14,318
This is great.

352
00:15:16,988 --> 00:15:19,027
Hye Yoon, doesn't it feel good to be lying down like that?

353
00:15:19,028 --> 00:15:20,828
- It feels amazing. - Really?

354
00:15:21,398 --> 00:15:22,498
I feel so happy.

355
00:15:22,868 --> 00:15:26,538
(At this moment, she can only hear the gentle sound of water.)

356
00:15:27,098 --> 00:15:29,508
(Are you happy?)

357
00:15:30,008 --> 00:15:31,868
Hye Yoon is treating me...

358
00:15:32,578 --> 00:15:34,338
like I'm her servant.

359
00:15:34,538 --> 00:15:35,577
Dex, what did you say?

360
00:15:35,578 --> 00:15:38,078
Nothing. Enjoy. You're on vacation.

361
00:15:38,918 --> 00:15:40,978
(Fully enjoying her vacation)

362
00:15:41,448 --> 00:15:43,588
(Staring)

363
00:15:44,018 --> 00:15:47,218
(Let's drop Hye Yoon in the water.)

364
00:15:47,688 --> 00:15:50,028
(Suddenly, Dex gets mischievous.)

365
00:15:50,528 --> 00:15:52,597
(The operation kicks off.)

366
00:15:52,598 --> 00:15:54,928
Gosh. Do not worry.

367
00:15:55,158 --> 00:15:56,168
Okay.

368
00:15:56,798 --> 00:15:59,868
(Approaching quietly after reassuring her)

369
00:16:00,338 --> 00:16:01,668
Is he going to undo her board?

370
00:16:02,208 --> 00:16:03,238
To make her fall in the water.

371
00:16:03,868 --> 00:16:04,937
Since we're almost there...

372
00:16:04,938 --> 00:16:06,408
To drop her in the water by flipping it.

373
00:16:06,778 --> 00:16:08,608
- No way. - To drop her in the water.

374
00:16:09,108 --> 00:16:12,148
(He approaches Hye Yoon who has no idea.)

375
00:16:15,888 --> 00:16:17,588
(Glug-glug)

376
00:16:17,788 --> 00:16:20,788
(Hye Yoon, isn't it refreshing?)

377
00:16:21,088 --> 00:16:22,458
What's wrong with Dex?

378
00:16:23,488 --> 00:16:24,587
Dex.

379
00:16:24,588 --> 00:16:26,027
(Thanks to Dex, her last dive was refreshing.)

380
00:16:26,028 --> 00:16:27,928
How could you do this to me?

381
00:16:30,568 --> 00:16:31,568
He's so excited.

382
00:16:31,569 --> 00:16:34,198
(A vacation that everyone enjoyed together)

383
00:16:35,098 --> 00:16:37,208
(Another memory got added.)

384
00:16:37,638 --> 00:16:40,308
It was so much fun. I'll sleep very well tonight again.

385
00:16:41,078 --> 00:16:43,778
We're here.

386
00:16:44,708 --> 00:16:46,678
- Thank you. - Thank you.

387
00:16:48,018 --> 00:16:49,018
I'm tired.
(Staggering)

388
00:16:50,018 --> 00:16:51,018
You look quite exhausted.

389
00:16:51,019 --> 00:16:52,787
She looks very tired.

390
00:16:52,788 --> 00:16:53,818
I'm knocked out.

391
00:16:57,458 --> 00:16:58,528
Are they giving us food?

392
00:16:58,928 --> 00:17:01,658
(Her eyes light up again at the mention of food.)

393
00:17:01,958 --> 00:17:06,197
Dive into the Jungle package includes lunch.

394
00:17:06,198 --> 00:17:07,938
- That's nice. - Is that so?

395
00:17:08,598 --> 00:17:09,607
(Exclaiming)

396
00:17:09,608 --> 00:17:11,538
(Local food to satisfy their hunger after playing in the water)

397
00:17:11,808 --> 00:17:14,008
What will be the local food in the Philippines?

398
00:17:14,438 --> 00:17:16,248
Jun Myun, didn't you swallow some water at the end?

399
00:17:16,508 --> 00:17:17,607
Did you swallow some water?

400
00:17:17,608 --> 00:17:20,648
I thought that something went wrong because you weren't moving.

401
00:17:21,478 --> 00:17:22,717
She was just floating.

402
00:17:22,718 --> 00:17:24,818
I also thought that you were exhausted.

403
00:17:28,588 --> 00:17:32,198
(Spacing out)

404
00:17:32,228 --> 00:17:34,297
- When we saw you from afar... - No, I was...

405
00:17:34,298 --> 00:17:35,828
relying on Dex.

406
00:17:36,198 --> 00:17:37,567
- He was pulling me. - She was enjoying herself.

407
00:17:37,568 --> 00:17:39,638
I was enjoying myself while leaning back.

408
00:17:41,538 --> 00:17:43,608
Food is here. I can't wait.

409
00:17:43,708 --> 00:17:45,878
Are you hungry? You must be very hungry.

410
00:17:46,278 --> 00:17:47,338
Gosh, it's chicken.

411
00:17:48,208 --> 00:17:50,348
I see. It's chicken over rice.

412
00:17:51,208 --> 00:17:53,218
(Exclaiming with excitement)

413
00:17:53,918 --> 00:17:59,488
(A generous serving topped with a big chicken leg)

414
00:18:00,358 --> 00:18:01,558
(Exclaiming)

415
00:18:02,588 --> 00:18:03,628
Look at the side dishes.

416
00:18:04,188 --> 00:18:06,858
- Gosh, isn't it japchae? - Is it japchae?

417
00:18:06,958 --> 00:18:09,097
- It looks like japchae. - Right.

418
00:18:09,098 --> 00:18:10,867
(From a noodle dish that looks like japchae...)

419
00:18:10,868 --> 00:18:16,008
(to stir-fried meat dishes that look appetizing)

420
00:18:16,868 --> 00:18:21,378
(A hearty Filipino meal to enjoy after playing in the water)

421
00:18:25,208 --> 00:18:26,478
Thank you for the food.

422
00:18:26,918 --> 00:18:28,718
Bon appetit.

423
00:18:29,348 --> 00:18:32,318
(Grabbing some chicken first with a fork)

424
00:18:32,888 --> 00:18:35,088
(Eating a big piece)

425
00:18:36,058 --> 00:18:37,888
Gosh, the chicken tastes good.

426
00:18:38,188 --> 00:18:39,328
- Really? - Yes.

427
00:18:41,158 --> 00:18:42,697
(Hye Yoon also takes a big bite because she's hungry.)

428
00:18:42,698 --> 00:18:45,168
The chicken is delicious. It tastes light.

429
00:18:45,898 --> 00:18:47,267
- It's nice and lean. - Really?

430
00:18:47,268 --> 00:18:48,268
Yes.

431
00:18:48,498 --> 00:18:50,707
(Marinated chicken in a sauce that's made...)

432
00:18:50,708 --> 00:18:53,038
(with local ingredients such as calamansi and coconut vinegar)

433
00:18:53,878 --> 00:19:00,647
(Grilled with the fat drained out, making it even tastier)

434
00:19:00,648 --> 00:19:02,147
This is quite good.

435
00:19:02,148 --> 00:19:05,218
It's the best thing I've eaten here so far.

436
00:19:06,488 --> 00:19:10,488
(Chicken inasal)

437
00:19:12,058 --> 00:19:13,697
(With fat drained out, it tastes light and savory.)

438
00:19:13,698 --> 00:19:14,698
It's good.
- Do you like it? - Yes.

439
00:19:16,068 --> 00:19:19,798
(You can't stop eating it because it's not greasy.)

440
00:19:20,068 --> 00:19:21,137
It's a holiday.

441
00:19:21,138 --> 00:19:23,938
(The lunch tastes even better after playing in the water.)

442
00:19:25,438 --> 00:19:26,438
(Chicken)

443
00:19:26,638 --> 00:19:28,077
(And Hye Yoon is devouring with gusto.)

444
00:19:28,078 --> 00:19:29,078
(More chicken)

445
00:19:29,079 --> 00:19:31,348
(And Hye Yoon is devouring with gusto.)

446
00:19:32,548 --> 00:19:35,318
(Eating a heap of rice that's bigger than her mouth)

447
00:19:36,188 --> 00:19:40,688
(She must've been very hungry after playing in the water.)

448
00:19:41,318 --> 00:19:43,487
(It's delicious.)

449
00:19:43,488 --> 00:19:44,958
This is really great.

450
00:19:46,358 --> 00:19:48,198
(Happy)

451
00:19:49,228 --> 00:19:50,897
- Did you have fun? - Yes.

452
00:19:50,898 --> 00:19:52,228
(Feeling proud)

453
00:19:52,338 --> 00:19:55,168
Food tastes good after playing in the water.

454
00:19:56,008 --> 00:19:57,068
What should we do?

455
00:19:57,168 --> 00:19:58,537
Brainstorm some ideas.

456
00:19:58,538 --> 00:19:59,538
For the game?

457
00:19:59,539 --> 00:20:01,008
Tomorrow... What is it called?

458
00:20:01,108 --> 00:20:03,248
- The meal coupon? - The middle-end lunch.

459
00:20:03,508 --> 00:20:05,848
Let's play a team game...

460
00:20:06,248 --> 00:20:07,778
like telepathy.

461
00:20:09,318 --> 00:20:11,348
(This morning, Jung Ah was staring at the schedule.)

462
00:20:11,488 --> 00:20:13,118
Why is there a middle-end meal coupon?

463
00:20:14,188 --> 00:20:17,258
(Jung Ah put up the middle-end meal coupon.)

464
00:20:17,688 --> 00:20:20,758
We have to win the middle-end meal coupon tomorrow.

465
00:20:21,198 --> 00:20:23,467
Let's propose a game today.

466
00:20:23,468 --> 00:20:24,567
Okay, the middle-end...

467
00:20:24,568 --> 00:20:25,968
A game that we can win.

468
00:20:27,468 --> 00:20:29,808
Let's make it clean and play a 5-on-5 team game.

469
00:20:30,108 --> 00:20:32,537
- Is it too... - How about Guess Who?

470
00:20:32,538 --> 00:20:33,977
Guess Who?

471
00:20:33,978 --> 00:20:35,337
- Dex can't do it. - I can't.

472
00:20:35,338 --> 00:20:36,347
He's bad at Guess Who.

473
00:20:36,348 --> 00:20:37,847
- I can't remember names... - He doesn't know many people.

474
00:20:37,848 --> 00:20:40,477
He probably can't guess correctly even if it's Hye Yoon.

475
00:20:40,478 --> 00:20:42,278
- Oh, my gosh. He'd say Hye Won. - Hye Yoon...

476
00:20:42,388 --> 00:20:44,117
"Kim Hye Won." Fail.

477
00:20:44,118 --> 00:20:45,118
(Let's not play Guess Who.)

478
00:20:45,119 --> 00:20:48,818
There's a game we prepared with a coin at stake.

479
00:20:49,288 --> 00:20:51,858
It's jumping rope with acupressure slippers.

480
00:20:53,328 --> 00:20:54,927
How can you jump rope with slippers on?

481
00:20:54,928 --> 00:20:56,267
- It's impossible with regular ones. - Acupressure...

482
00:20:56,268 --> 00:20:57,627
How many jumps?

483
00:20:57,628 --> 00:20:59,698
A total of 30 jumps together.

484
00:21:00,298 --> 00:21:01,468
We can totally do it.

485
00:21:02,238 --> 00:21:03,337
- Can you do it... - We can totally do 50.

486
00:21:03,338 --> 00:21:04,807
- I think we can do it. - All together...

487
00:21:04,808 --> 00:21:05,908
A total of 30 together?

488
00:21:06,108 --> 00:21:08,377
(If you succeed, we'll give you a middle-end meal coupon.)

489
00:21:08,378 --> 00:21:09,807
Seriously? Okay.

490
00:21:09,808 --> 00:21:10,908
That's a piece of cake.

491
00:21:11,008 --> 00:21:12,208
Let's do it right here.

492
00:21:12,578 --> 00:21:13,918
Shall we do it now?

493
00:21:15,178 --> 00:21:16,717
(Their confidence lasted only briefly.)

494
00:21:16,718 --> 00:21:18,948
(Moaning)

495
00:21:19,188 --> 00:21:20,188
(Screaming)

496
00:21:20,818 --> 00:21:22,118
(Take them off.)

497
00:21:22,528 --> 00:21:24,588
(This is abuse.)

498
00:21:24,828 --> 00:21:27,558
(What will be the result of the most painful game ever?)

499
00:21:28,258 --> 00:21:30,427
Before you play the game,

500
00:21:30,428 --> 00:21:32,597
remember the local invigorating food that you won last time?

501
00:21:32,598 --> 00:21:34,767
- Yes. - As a dessert...

502
00:21:34,768 --> 00:21:36,437
- That sounds good. - Invigorating food as a dessert?

503
00:21:36,438 --> 00:21:38,537
Si Eon, it's a good thing. It's not a penalty.

504
00:21:38,538 --> 00:21:40,438
It's not a penalty. It's a present.

505
00:21:41,808 --> 00:21:43,577
(A coin they got after catching alimango...)

506
00:21:43,578 --> 00:21:45,708
(while completely covered in mud)

507
00:21:46,048 --> 00:21:47,948
(Drawn with the coin)

508
00:21:48,148 --> 00:21:52,658
(A present-like local invigorating food)

509
00:21:54,588 --> 00:21:55,888
What's the matter?

510
00:21:57,658 --> 00:21:58,688
Could these be duck eggs?

511
00:21:59,298 --> 00:22:00,298
What are these?

512
00:22:01,128 --> 00:22:02,128
What?

513
00:22:02,328 --> 00:22:03,468
They look like duck eggs.

514
00:22:04,898 --> 00:22:05,898
What are they?

515
00:22:05,899 --> 00:22:07,398
(Mysterious duck eggs appear.)

516
00:22:07,738 --> 00:22:09,168
It's making me feel anxious.

517
00:22:09,738 --> 00:22:12,068
- Is it a penalty? - It shouldn't be a penalty.

518
00:22:12,938 --> 00:22:14,007
- What are these? - What are these?

519
00:22:14,008 --> 00:22:17,247
- Some sort of eggs? - They're called balut.

520
00:22:17,248 --> 00:22:20,318
They're Filipino-style fermented eggs.

521
00:22:20,918 --> 00:22:22,548
Let's not eat these. They'll be like fermented skate.

522
00:22:22,648 --> 00:22:24,518
- Fermented skate? - They're like fermented skate.

523
00:22:24,748 --> 00:22:25,748
Are these chicken eggs?

524
00:22:26,318 --> 00:22:27,617
No, they're duck eggs.

525
00:22:27,618 --> 00:22:29,288
They look exactly like duck eggs.

526
00:22:30,058 --> 00:22:31,058
(Invigorating food that Filipinos eat on important days)

527
00:22:31,059 --> 00:22:34,158
(Scared)

528
00:22:34,198 --> 00:22:35,198
Mark.

529
00:22:35,298 --> 00:22:36,997
Hey, Assigned Marker.

530
00:22:36,998 --> 00:22:38,128
(Mark who's a local arrives.)

531
00:22:38,228 --> 00:22:39,938
Try it. How do we eat it?

532
00:22:40,338 --> 00:22:41,498
How do we eat it?

533
00:22:43,908 --> 00:22:47,378
(Roughly cracking the top of the egg with his hand)

534
00:22:48,208 --> 00:22:50,478
- Is there something inside? - A baby...

535
00:22:50,708 --> 00:22:51,848
(Exclaiming)

536
00:22:52,048 --> 00:22:54,777
(Making a fuss even when he drops it)

537
00:22:54,778 --> 00:22:55,848
Now...

