00:43:54,858 --> 00:43:59,028
(When they enjoy the food so much like that...)

1062
00:44:03,368 --> 00:44:04,368
(Laughing)

1063
00:44:04,369 --> 00:44:06,238
- We aren't saying a word. - Not even a word. Seriously.

1064
00:44:06,338 --> 00:44:07,368
Isn't it ridiculous?

1065
00:44:07,538 --> 00:44:11,077
We're way more excited, compared to the low-end restaurant.

1066
00:44:11,078 --> 00:44:12,978
We used the high-end meal coupon, indeed.

1067
00:44:13,078 --> 00:44:15,408
- It's so tasty, so... - So we keep eating.

1068
00:44:16,478 --> 00:44:18,548
(And at that moment,)

1069
00:44:21,218 --> 00:44:23,088
(Jun Myun takes out a piece of mango from the juice.)

1070
00:44:23,448 --> 00:44:25,218
(She grabs a mango in the drink.)

1071
00:44:25,318 --> 00:44:26,617
(All eyes are on her.)

1072
00:44:26,618 --> 00:44:27,627
Are you eating that mango?

1073
00:44:27,628 --> 00:44:28,728
Did you find that mango?

1074
00:44:29,158 --> 00:44:30,457
Where did you find the mango?

1075
00:44:30,458 --> 00:44:31,458
- Where was it? - Gosh.
I should eat this piece that was in the juice.

1076
00:44:32,459 --> 00:44:33,558
You should.

1077
00:44:34,398 --> 00:44:36,828
(I won't let go of even a tiny piece of mango.)

1078
00:44:37,438 --> 00:44:38,698
It turns me into a mango aficionado.

1079
00:44:40,038 --> 00:44:41,168
I'm crazy about mangos.

1080
00:44:41,768 --> 00:44:43,767
Jung Ah, it's really tasty, though.

1081
00:44:43,768 --> 00:44:44,808
(She has upgraded from Mango Park to a mango aficionado.)

1082
00:44:44,908 --> 00:44:45,908
What?

1083
00:44:47,648 --> 00:44:49,408
- Gosh. Mango aficiando. - Park Jun Myun!

1084
00:44:51,648 --> 00:44:53,618
(Wide-eyed)

1085
00:44:54,088 --> 00:44:56,118
(For Jun Myun,)

1086
00:44:56,518 --> 00:44:59,588
(a bunch of mangos is served.)

1087
00:45:00,688 --> 00:45:02,927
(It feels like she owns the world.)

1088
00:45:02,928 --> 00:45:04,257
(She's happy already.)

1089
00:45:04,258 --> 00:45:06,597
She picked the yellowest piece.

1090
00:45:06,598 --> 00:45:10,267
(Eating the yellow mango)

1091
00:45:10,268 --> 00:45:11,838
- Nice. - Gosh.

1092
00:45:12,638 --> 00:45:14,638
I mean, she looks so happy.

1093
00:45:15,438 --> 00:45:16,508
It's so good, Jung Ah.

1094
00:45:17,408 --> 00:45:19,078
Apple mangos don't even come close.

1095
00:45:19,838 --> 00:45:20,878
These Filipino mangos.

1096
00:45:21,648 --> 00:45:22,648
(Sucking)

1097
00:45:22,649 --> 00:45:25,418
You have to pay 25 dollars to get a good mango...

1098
00:45:25,948 --> 00:45:27,847
- Right. You told me that. - at a department store.

1099
00:45:27,848 --> 00:45:28,848
(Right. You said the same thing last time.)

1100
00:45:29,518 --> 00:45:33,788
(She's lost in a mango bliss.)

1101
00:45:34,358 --> 00:45:36,888
(Dex takes a bite of a well-ripened mango.)

1102
00:45:37,728 --> 00:45:41,428
(Si Eon grabs one too.)

1103
00:45:42,228 --> 00:45:44,468
(The brothers play the harmonicas made of mangos.)

1104
00:45:45,438 --> 00:45:47,968
(Hye Yoon takes a bite too.)

1105
00:45:48,968 --> 00:45:51,408
(Jun Myun sucks the last piece of the mango.)

1106
00:45:51,578 --> 00:45:53,237
I devoured them in seconds.

1107
00:45:53,238 --> 00:45:54,907
(They finish eating the satisfying meal.)

1108
00:45:54,908 --> 00:45:56,648
- We didn't even talk. - No.

1109
00:45:57,278 --> 00:46:00,348
- You had a fun day today, right? - Yes.

1110
00:46:00,918 --> 00:46:03,787
Let me tell you about tomorrow's schedule again.

1111
00:46:03,788 --> 00:46:05,287
It's the day of Fun Exploration...

1112
00:46:05,288 --> 00:46:06,818
- "Fun." Yes. - of Local Crops.

1113
00:46:07,158 --> 00:46:10,588
(Did you say Fun Exploration of Local Crops?)

1114
00:46:11,358 --> 00:46:13,328
(The Philippines is full of various crops.)

1115
00:46:14,668 --> 00:46:18,938
(Which crop will they explore and have fun?)

1116
00:46:19,168 --> 00:46:20,597
You'll have fun tomorrow.

1117
00:46:20,598 --> 00:46:23,037
Really? I really hope it'll be fun.

1118
00:46:23,038 --> 00:46:25,338
(Will we be able to have fun?)

1119
00:46:26,338 --> 00:46:28,747
- We came back home after so long. - That's true.

1120
00:46:28,748 --> 00:46:30,048
Jung Ah, I'll wash up first.

1121
00:46:30,148 --> 00:46:31,178
- Okay. - Okay.

1122
00:46:33,418 --> 00:46:34,617
(The older sisters come out to the living room...)

1123
00:46:34,618 --> 00:46:35,817
(after showering first.)

1124
00:46:35,818 --> 00:46:37,088
Play some music.

1125
00:46:37,658 --> 00:46:38,787
My type of music?

1126
00:46:38,788 --> 00:46:40,418
- Yes. Your type of music. - Okay.

1127
00:46:40,618 --> 00:46:42,358
Something sexy.

1128
00:46:44,028 --> 00:46:45,527
I'll go with my type of music.

1129
00:46:45,528 --> 00:46:47,358
(Music will be to Jun Myun's taste.)

1130
00:46:48,068 --> 00:46:50,098
(A simple wine party for just two of them after a while)

1131
00:46:51,038 --> 00:46:52,038
Well done, Jung Ah.

1132
00:46:52,768 --> 00:46:54,838
- It was fun. - Wasn't it fun?

1133
00:46:55,308 --> 00:46:58,978
(They chat and sip wine alternately while facing each other.)

1134
00:46:59,108 --> 00:47:00,637
- It was mango juice. - Yes.

1135
00:47:00,638 --> 00:47:01,907
(The two are absorbed in their conversation.)

1136
00:47:01,908 --> 00:47:03,578
(Singing)

1137
00:47:04,678 --> 00:47:07,047
- It was less hot. - It was.

1138
00:47:07,048 --> 00:47:08,888
The house was nice too.

1139
00:47:09,718 --> 00:47:11,258
Where is this singer from?

1140
00:47:11,988 --> 00:47:14,428
(Laughing)

1141
00:47:14,628 --> 00:47:16,057
- I got it, Jung Ah. - No.

1142
00:47:16,058 --> 00:47:17,958
- Is it okay? - I like it.

1143
00:47:18,458 --> 00:47:23,528
(If you like it, I like it too, Jun Myun.)

1144
00:47:23,928 --> 00:47:26,468
(It's so nice.)

1145
00:47:31,678 --> 00:47:37,078
(Just listening to the song makes them laugh.)

1146
00:47:37,248 --> 00:47:38,517
- I mean... - Okay.

1147
00:47:38,518 --> 00:47:40,347
It's a bit hardcore. I'll listen to it when I'm alone.

1148
00:47:40,348 --> 00:47:42,448
- Jung Ah, this is hardcore. - Gosh, Jun Myun.

1149
00:47:43,548 --> 00:47:44,717
Hello.

1150
00:47:44,718 --> 00:47:45,858
Hey. Come in.

1151
00:47:46,418 --> 00:47:47,987
Dex took too long to shower.

1152
00:47:47,988 --> 00:47:51,027
(They're gathered like always at night in the Philippines.)

1153
00:47:51,028 --> 00:47:53,557
Gosh, Jun Myun. Why does my arm hurt so bad?

1154
00:47:53,558 --> 00:47:56,468
- Is it from yesterday? - Because you kept pulling it.

1155
00:47:57,768 --> 00:48:00,638
I went, "Gosh. Let's see who will win."

1156
00:48:00,968 --> 00:48:03,538
(That's true.)

1157
00:48:03,708 --> 00:48:06,538
Everything was fun. The weather has been great too.

1158
00:48:06,738 --> 00:48:09,047
Personally, I loved the fireflies.

1159
00:48:09,048 --> 00:48:11,647
The quietness felt like a break.

1160
00:48:11,648 --> 00:48:13,018
And they light up.

1161
00:48:13,978 --> 00:48:17,717
Jung Ah. Seriously. A yellow turtle came up this close,

1162
00:48:17,718 --> 00:48:19,017
and it was so impressive.

1163
00:48:19,018 --> 00:48:20,688
That turtle was adorable.

1164
00:48:20,918 --> 00:48:22,627
I loved yesterday's dinner.

1165
00:48:22,628 --> 00:48:23,628
- It was great. - Yes.

1166
00:48:23,728 --> 00:48:26,258
It was even better than today's dinner.

1167
00:48:27,198 --> 00:48:28,228
- Jung Ah. - Because it was different.

1168
00:48:28,898 --> 00:48:30,768
- If you were... - Yes?

1169
00:48:31,068 --> 00:48:34,038
to travel, is there someone you want to go with?

1170
00:48:34,868 --> 00:48:37,638
If I weren't coming, who do you want to go with?

1171
00:48:37,808 --> 00:48:39,337
Do you think I would think of traveling...

1172
00:48:39,338 --> 00:48:41,477
- someone other than you? - Come on.

1173
00:48:41,478 --> 00:48:43,477
I'm here because of you.

1174
00:48:43,478 --> 00:48:44,948
- I mean... - Dex.

1175
00:48:45,148 --> 00:48:47,148
You set the standard.

1176
00:48:47,748 --> 00:48:50,617
- Because he set the standard, - Gosh. It's crazy.

1177
00:48:50,618 --> 00:48:54,058
he's the perfect one for me.

1178
00:48:54,988 --> 00:48:58,858
(He's melting from the big sister's non-stop compliments.)

1179
00:48:59,258 --> 00:49:02,828
(He can't help it.)

1180
00:49:03,398 --> 00:49:04,997
(This is...)

1181
00:49:04,998 --> 00:49:07,168
(the attitude of the youngest one who is perfect.)

1182
00:49:07,368 --> 00:49:08,568
Did you see that, Hye Yoon?

1183
00:49:09,608 --> 00:49:10,808
I'm the OG youngest.

1184
00:49:11,538 --> 00:49:13,838
I'm quite competent myself.

1185
00:49:14,608 --> 00:49:16,747
I realized this time how capable you are.

1186
00:49:16,748 --> 00:49:18,448
I'm quite sharp myself.

1187
00:49:19,248 --> 00:49:20,248
(I can't let him slide.)

1188
00:49:20,249 --> 00:49:21,318
(Laughing)

1189
00:49:21,588 --> 00:49:23,587
I should practice dancing.

1190
00:49:23,588 --> 00:49:25,888
- Yes. - Really? Are you going to show us?

1191
00:49:26,958 --> 00:49:27,958
I can't believe her.

1192
00:49:27,959 --> 00:49:30,058
(The young ones are hilarious.)

1193
00:49:30,258 --> 00:49:32,097
Actually, I'm doing "BANG BANG,"

1194
00:49:32,098 --> 00:49:33,458
as a challenge.

1195
00:49:34,128 --> 00:49:35,128
(Posing)

1196
00:49:35,368 --> 00:49:37,268
(The big brother laughs at her at first.)

1197
00:49:37,528 --> 00:49:39,338
Good job.

1198
00:49:40,098 --> 00:49:41,138
Do you want me to play the song?

1199
00:49:41,668 --> 00:49:42,668
Yes, please.

1200
00:49:42,669 --> 00:49:44,068
Let's start "BANG BANG."

1201
00:49:44,908 --> 00:49:47,108
(The original youngest sibling has become very arrogant.)

1202
00:49:47,538 --> 00:49:48,947
(Standing in front of him alone...)

1203
00:49:48,948 --> 00:49:50,108
(is the current youngest sibling.)

1204
00:49:54,248 --> 00:49:55,487
- She's good. - It's not bad.

1205
00:49:55,488 --> 00:49:56,518
She has gotten better.

1206
00:49:56,688 --> 00:49:57,958
Bang bang

1207
00:49:58,658 --> 00:49:59,988
(Impressed)

1208
00:50:00,258 --> 00:50:02,158
(She lit up the room with a bang.)

1209
00:50:02,488 --> 00:50:05,627
(This is what the current youngest sibling can do.)

1210
00:50:05,628 --> 00:50:06,758
Thank you.

1211
00:50:07,028 --> 00:50:08,367
(Giving a big hand for the main dancer of the show)

1212
00:50:08,368 --> 00:50:09,598
You were good.

1213
00:50:09,798 --> 00:50:11,267
You were really good.

1214
00:50:11,268 --> 00:50:13,098
Hye Yoon is no ordinary girl.

1215
00:50:13,668 --> 00:50:15,468
I'm sorry I didn't notice it before.

1216
00:50:15,938 --> 00:50:18,177
Do you know what it just felt like?

1217
00:50:18,178 --> 00:50:21,907
It's a holiday. And a five-year-old is showing...

1218
00:50:21,908 --> 00:50:24,008
what she learned from the kindergarten.

1219
00:50:24,108 --> 00:50:25,617
That was how it felt.

1220
00:50:25,618 --> 00:50:27,077
I should give you ten dollars, then.

1221
00:50:27,078 --> 00:50:28,088
(Feeling holiday spirits in the Philippines)

1222
00:50:28,418 --> 00:50:31,617
Hye Yoon, I'm glad I got to know you this time.

1223
00:50:31,618 --> 00:50:32,618
Right?

1224
00:50:32,818 --> 00:50:36,057
- I hope to see you again one day. - Yes.

1225
00:50:36,058 --> 00:50:37,058
Seriously.

1226
00:50:37,628 --> 00:50:38,628
(Jun Myun and Si Eon costarred in a drama before.)

1227
00:50:38,629 --> 00:50:39,928
Why? What is it, Si Eon?

1228
00:50:40,598 --> 00:50:42,498
I didn't know how to film a kissing scene.

1229
00:50:42,728 --> 00:50:44,967
I hadn't played such a scene due to my characters.

1230
00:50:44,968 --> 00:50:47,367
I always get yelled at, like "What are you looking at?"

1231
00:50:47,368 --> 00:50:48,808
(His sad characters always looked at something.)

1232
00:50:48,868 --> 00:50:50,767
- You never had a kissing scene? - I had once.

1233
00:50:50,768 --> 00:50:52,008
(Pointing)

1234
00:50:52,678 --> 00:50:54,038
Did you have a kissing scene with Jun Myun?

1235
00:50:55,008 --> 00:50:57,777
What kind of nonsense is that? What are you talking about?

1236
00:50:57,778 --> 00:51:00,578
- I mean... - Jun Myun, why are you so angry?

1237
00:51:00,748 --> 00:51:01,848
I mean...

1238
00:51:01,948 --> 00:51:04,118
- He pointed at her. - Do you hate it that much?

1239
00:51:04,858 --> 00:51:07,018
(What's wrong with you all?)

1240
00:51:07,188 --> 00:51:08,787
You had a kissing scene in a drama you costarred with her.

1241
00:51:08,788 --> 00:51:10,328
- Yes. - You had it in there.

1242
00:51:12,298 --> 00:51:13,357
Gosh. Good.

1243
00:51:13,358 --> 00:51:14,527
(Drinking wine after clearing her name)

1244
00:51:14,528 --> 00:51:16,028
When are we getting up tomorrow?

1245
00:51:16,228 --> 00:51:17,427
We're leaving at 9am.

1246
00:51:17,428 --> 00:51:18,567
Then I need to get up at 8am.

1247
00:51:18,568 --> 00:51:19,568
We can wake up at 8am.

1248
00:51:19,668 --> 00:51:23,108
- Fun Exploration of Local Crops. - Yes.

1249
00:51:23,408 --> 00:51:24,637
What on earth is that?

1250
00:51:24,638 --> 00:51:27,008
(What is that now?)

1251
00:51:27,338 --> 00:51:28,448
Half-labor?

1252
00:51:28,648 --> 00:51:29,947
- Full labor. - Is that it?

1253
00:51:29,948 --> 00:51:30,978
Yes. Labor.

1254
00:51:31,418 --> 00:51:32,447
Should we pack some food, then?

1255
00:51:32,448 --> 00:51:33,718
(Should we pack some food, then?)

1256
00:51:33,778 --> 00:51:35,917
Okay. We have to dance before we leave.

1257
00:51:35,918 --> 00:51:37,048
(Stop worrying yet, Jung Ah. Let's dance before we leave.)

1258
00:51:37,388 --> 00:51:39,018
(Dancing out of the blue)

1259
00:51:39,288 --> 00:51:40,288
It's the last night.

1260
00:51:40,388 --> 00:51:41,487
My goodness.

1261
00:51:41,488 --> 00:51:42,987
There are some balloons.

1262
00:51:42,988 --> 00:51:44,187
There are balloons.

1263
00:51:44,188 --> 00:51:45,898
(The dance party on the last night comes to an end.)

1264
00:51:46,658 --> 00:51:50,028
(When the dazzling sunlight shines upon the siblings' house,)

1265
00:51:51,938 --> 00:51:54,607
(dancing waves...)

1266
00:51:54,608 --> 00:51:57,938
(and dancing people welcome...)

1267
00:51:58,738 --> 00:52:02,308
(the exceptionally enjoyable morning.)

1268
00:52:03,108 --> 00:52:07,848
(How will today shine?)

1269
00:52:08,288 --> 00:52:09,387
(The siblings get ready to set off.)

1270
00:52:09,388 --> 00:52:10,388
You look cute.

1271
00:52:11,818 --> 00:52:13,218
Should I wear my cap?

1272
00:52:13,718 --> 00:52:15,827
I plan to bring the straw hat today.

1273
00:52:15,828 --> 00:52:16,858
Me too.

1274
00:52:17,228 --> 00:52:19,027
(The newbie Si Eon follows Dex, who joined the show before him.)

1275
00:52:19,028 --> 00:52:21,158
- We're on the same wavelength. - Really?

1276
00:52:21,498 --> 00:52:22,727
We should bring this.

1277
00:52:22,728 --> 00:52:24,498
We must bring all of these no matter what.

1278
00:52:25,098 --> 00:52:27,638
Even if we end up not eating them, we should still bring them.

1279
00:52:27,868 --> 00:52:29,738
I think they'll finish the eggs.

1280
00:52:30,308 --> 00:52:31,337
Let's go.

1281
00:52:31,338 --> 00:52:33,008
(They pack one whole bag full and walk out.)

1282
00:52:33,508 --> 00:52:35,707
(Are they still asleep?)

1283
00:52:35,708 --> 00:52:37,148
- Yes? - Dex!

1284
00:52:37,348 --> 00:52:39,118
- Yes? - Si Eon, let's go.

1285
00:52:39,218 --> 00:52:40,248
Okay.

1286
00:52:40,648 --> 00:52:41,717
Are you done?

1287
00:52:41,718 --> 00:52:42,847
(He responds to Jung Ah's loud morning call...)

1288
00:52:42,848 --> 00:52:44,417
(with his fully-dressed self.)

1289
00:52:44,418 --> 00:52:45,557
Nice.

1290
00:52:45,558 --> 00:52:47,417
- You look cute wearing that. - I found it in the room.

1291
00:52:47,418 --> 00:52:48,788
Yes. You look nice.

1292
00:52:48,928 --> 00:52:50,027
Good morning.

1293
00:52:50,028 --> 00:52:51,127
- Good morning. - Good morning.

1294
00:52:51,128 --> 00:52:52,828
(Dex hurriedly joins them too.)

1295
00:52:53,328 --> 00:52:56,268
- Let's go. - Shall we go?

1296
00:52:57,128 --> 00:52:59,568
(Dex will drive today again!)

1297
00:52:59,838 --> 00:53:01,267
I made some boiled eggs,

1298
00:53:01,268 --> 00:53:03,038
so let me know if you want one.

1299
00:53:03,408 --> 00:53:04,508
This early in the morning?

1300
00:53:05,778 --> 00:53:08,277
- You don't have salt, do you? - I didn't bring it.

1301
00:53:08,278 --> 00:53:10,547
(So there's no salt for the eggs.)

1302
00:53:10,548 --> 00:53:11,778
Do you need salt?

1303
00:53:12,448 --> 00:53:15,118
- No, it's fine. - Should I run back and get it?

1304
00:53:15,588 --> 00:53:16,618
It's all right.

1305
00:53:18,918 --> 00:53:19,958
I feel so happy.

1306
00:53:20,188 --> 00:53:21,657
I wonder where we're going.

1307
00:53:21,658 --> 00:53:22,757
(They set off to explore the local crops,)

1308
00:53:22,758 --> 00:53:23,758
(and the thought of it makes them happy already.)

1309
00:53:24,028 --> 00:53:25,528
- Can I eat one? - Try it.

1310
00:53:26,198 --> 00:53:27,628
Is it overcooked?

1311
00:53:27,998 --> 00:53:29,097
I couldn't even control the heat.

1312
00:53:29,098 --> 00:53:30,467
It's half-boiled. Gosh, it's so well-cooked.

1313
00:53:30,468 --> 00:53:31,538
It's well-cooked.

1314
00:53:32,438 --> 00:53:33,697
I'll have one too.

1315
00:53:33,698 --> 00:53:35,467
- Thank you. - It's good.

1316
00:53:35,468 --> 00:53:37,807
Can I open the window?

1317
00:53:37,808 --> 00:53:38,838
Sure.

1318
00:53:39,138 --> 00:53:41,847
I smell a fart. You farted, right?

1319
00:53:41,848 --> 00:53:43,348
No, it was you.

1320
00:53:43,848 --> 00:53:46,048
Kids always fight over stuff like that. Right?

1321
00:53:46,278 --> 00:53:47,278
(What?)

1322
00:53:47,279 --> 00:53:49,488
(Give me that.)

1323
00:53:49,848 --> 00:53:50,848
(We...)

1324
00:53:50,849 --> 00:53:52,517
(don't fight.)

1325
00:53:52,518 --> 00:53:53,557
It tastes good...

1326
00:53:53,558 --> 00:53:54,588
- when you have it once in a while. - Yes.

1327
00:53:55,488 --> 00:53:56,557
This is so delicious.

1328
00:53:56,558 --> 00:53:58,557
(She eats the delicious egg in one bite!)

1329
00:53:58,558 --> 00:54:00,128
The egg yolk has an amazing color.

1330
00:54:01,428 --> 00:54:03,927
(Si Eon takes a big bite too!)

1331
00:54:03,928 --> 00:54:05,068
Why is this so tasty?

1332
00:54:05,568 --> 00:54:06,838
- I know, right? - It's insane.

1333
00:54:08,668 --> 00:54:09,768
It's delicious.

1334
00:54:10,168 --> 00:54:11,838
Did you go to a supermarket?

1335
00:54:12,278 --> 00:54:14,508
Yoon Gi's mom grew it in her garden.

1336
00:54:15,978 --> 00:54:17,148
You're so naughty.

1337
00:54:17,278 --> 00:54:18,848
Just looking at your eyes makes me laugh.

1338
00:54:19,078 --> 00:54:20,847
Jin Young was really cool yesterday.

1339
00:54:20,848 --> 00:54:23,148
When he entered the water and then came out,

1340
00:54:23,318 --> 00:54:26,618
he slicked his hair back with his hands like this.

1341
00:54:27,288 --> 00:54:28,857
He slicked his hair back.

1342
00:54:28,858 --> 00:54:31,598
(Yesterday's Dex in Paradise)

1343
00:54:31,828 --> 00:54:33,497
He slicked his hair back, and that reminded me...

1344
00:54:33,498 --> 00:54:34,828
of "I am Solo..."

1345
00:54:35,298 --> 00:54:37,498
- "I am Solo?" - Wait, not "I am Solo."

1346
00:54:38,038 --> 00:54:39,668
Was he like Yeong Cheol of "I am Solo?"

1347
00:54:40,298 --> 00:54:42,238
- "I am Solo." - Is it not "I am Solo?"

1348
00:54:42,408 --> 00:54:44,267
Not "I am Solo." I meant "Single's Inferno."

1349
00:54:44,268 --> 00:54:47,138
He showed off that fatal charm of his yesterday.

1350
00:54:47,738 --> 00:54:50,607
Jin Young looks good in both the water and the mountains.

1351
00:54:50,608 --> 00:54:52,748
- He looks the best there. - He's the coolest there.

1352
00:54:53,378 --> 00:54:54,378
(Snorting)

1353
00:54:54,379 --> 00:54:56,817
Hold on.

1354
00:54:56,818 --> 00:54:58,618
- I hear someone snorting. - No.

1355
00:54:58,788 --> 00:54:59,788
(Snorting)

1356
00:54:59,789 --> 00:55:02,358
(As they laugh and drive,)

1357
00:55:03,228 --> 00:55:04,487
(the wide roads and cars disappear.)

1358
00:55:04,488 --> 00:55:05,658
Are we almost there?

1359
00:55:05,928 --> 00:55:09,498
I think so. It took us exactly one and a half hours.

1360
00:55:11,228 --> 00:55:12,937
(They drive up...)

1361
00:55:12,938 --> 00:55:15,808
(the endless, bendy road.)

1362
00:55:16,868 --> 00:55:18,308
- The sea. - The sea.

1363
00:55:19,508 --> 00:55:21,038
- It's the sea. - How pretty.

1364
00:55:22,778 --> 00:55:23,977
It's so pretty.

1365
00:55:23,978 --> 00:55:25,677
- The sea and the sky. - It's really cool, isn't it?

1366
00:55:25,678 --> 00:55:27,878
(The blue Calape sea unfolds following the bendy mountain road.)

1367
00:55:30,218 --> 00:55:31,218
(But the more they drive...)

1368
00:55:31,219 --> 00:55:32,887
Oh, my.

1369
00:55:32,888 --> 00:55:34,117
(The car shakes harder.)

1370
00:55:34,118 --> 00:55:36,328
- What is this? - Jung Ah.

1371
00:55:37,588 --> 00:55:40,598
(Glancing)

1372
00:55:41,198 --> 00:55:44,028
(The car goes deeper into the forest.)

1373
00:55:44,568 --> 00:55:47,738
Wait, this is where we came on the first day.

1374
00:55:47,838 --> 00:55:48,838
- Really? - Yes.

1375
00:55:48,839 --> 00:55:50,407
We're going up that mountain road again?

1376
00:55:50,408 --> 00:55:51,507
We're at the entrance...

1377
00:55:51,508 --> 00:55:52,538
- of the mountain. - That's right.

1378
00:55:53,108 --> 00:55:54,707
(Now that you mention it...)

1379
00:55:54,708 --> 00:55:58,317
(2 days ago)

1380
00:55:58,318 --> 00:56:02,387
(Today)

1381
00:56:02,388 --> 00:56:05,517
(2 days ago)

1382
00:56:05,518 --> 00:56:08,328
(Today)

1383
00:56:08,788 --> 00:56:10,828
(They're scarily similar.)

1384
00:56:12,028 --> 00:56:14,098
Are we not done with pineapples and palm trees?

1385
00:56:14,158 --> 00:56:15,167
We didn't pick enough.

1386
00:56:15,168 --> 00:56:16,268
(We must've picked more.)

1387
00:56:16,468 --> 00:56:19,338
What other crops were on the way to that place?

1388
00:56:19,598 --> 00:56:22,738
Actually, besides coconuts,

1389
00:56:23,408 --> 00:56:25,838
I saw a monkey banana farm.

1390
00:56:26,308 --> 00:56:27,438
(Sighing)

1391
00:56:27,608 --> 00:56:28,777
Oh, my.

1392
00:56:28,778 --> 00:56:29,778
(Oh, my farm.)

1393
00:56:30,048 --> 00:56:31,948
A monkey banana farm.

1394
00:56:32,418 --> 00:56:34,577
There were many monkey bananas.

1395
00:56:34,578 --> 00:56:35,687
(A banana farm...)

1396
00:56:35,688 --> 00:56:38,158
- Maybe that. - They're lined up all the way.

1397
00:56:39,488 --> 00:56:42,127
- Where on earth are we going? - What labor will it be?

1398
00:56:42,128 --> 00:56:43,288
(When they escape the thick forest, some trees make their appearances.)

1399
00:56:44,628 --> 00:56:45,628
We must be here.

1400
00:56:45,629 --> 00:56:46,697
(They drive along the road on the mountaintop once again.)

1401
00:56:46,698 --> 00:56:48,598
Where is this now?

1402
00:56:48,968 --> 00:56:50,267
Let's get out.

1403
00:56:50,268 --> 00:56:52,137
- Thanks for driving. - Thanks for driving, really.

1404
00:56:52,138 --> 00:56:54,138
Where are we at?

1405
00:56:54,668 --> 00:56:57,308
I think these are bananas.

1406
00:56:58,838 --> 00:57:01,208
- Aren't they banana trees? - What? Banana trees?

1407
00:57:01,808 --> 00:57:02,493
Banana leaf.

1408
00:57:03,448 --> 00:57:04,607
We need to go down there?

1409
00:57:04,608 --> 00:57:08,588
(They walk down the trail.)

1410
00:57:10,084 --> 00:57:11,984
But there are coconuts here too.

1411
00:57:13,558 --> 00:57:15,488
The coconuts are so high up. Look at that.

1412
00:57:16,428 --> 00:57:18,557
- How do you pick that? - How do you get that?

1413
00:57:18,558 --> 00:57:20,028
- I wonder. - You can't.

1414
00:57:20,428 --> 00:57:21,528
That's no joke.

1415
00:57:22,598 --> 00:57:23,867
(Are they going to explore the coconuts further?)

1416
00:57:23,868 --> 00:57:25,238
That's so high up.

1417
00:57:27,568 --> 00:57:31,578
(They continue to walk down the trail.)

1418
00:57:32,078 --> 00:57:35,847
I feel like I'm walking on a rice field path in the countryside.

1419
00:57:35,848 --> 00:57:36,878
It totally feels like it.

1420
00:57:38,218 --> 00:57:40,778
Where's the crop?

1421
00:57:42,328 --> 00:57:43,658
Maybe it's not a fruit.

1422
00:57:44,048 --> 00:57:45,157
It looks like it.

1423
00:57:45,158 --> 00:57:46,918
(Perhaps the additional crop isn't a fruit?)

1424
00:57:53,398 --> 00:57:54,968
- What is it? - I...

1425
00:57:55,268 --> 00:57:55,772
What?

1426
00:57:57,228 --> 00:57:59,098
It's coconuts again.

1427
00:57:59,868 --> 00:58:00,968
Coconuts, right?

1428
00:58:05,578 --> 00:58:07,978
- There are coconuts all around. - Where is this?

1429
00:58:09,048 --> 00:58:10,507
How far must we go?

1430
00:58:10,508 --> 00:58:12,817
(How far must we go?)

1431
00:58:12,818 --> 00:58:13,948
Where are we going?

1432
00:58:14,648 --> 00:58:17,048
What are we exploring?

1433
00:58:18,438 --> 00:58:19,998
There's nothing to explore.

1434
00:58:23,028 --> 00:58:25,058
(Laughing in dismay)

1435
00:58:25,545 --> 00:58:27,145
There's nothing to explore.

1436
00:58:30,115 --> 00:58:32,125
(Laughing in dismay)

1437
00:58:34,770 --> 00:58:35,431
What's that?

1438
00:58:35,895 --> 00:58:38,824
(Something on top of the tree?)

1439
00:58:38,825 --> 00:58:39,562
What's this?

1440
00:58:40,695 --> 00:58:42,194
- My goodness. - What?

1441
00:58:42,195 --> 00:58:43,295
They're bananas.

1442
00:58:45,805 --> 00:58:46,805
My goodness.
(They spot bananas.)

1443
00:58:47,805 --> 00:58:48,805
They're so green, though.

1444
00:58:48,806 --> 00:58:49,874
(They spot green bananas.)

1445
00:58:49,875 --> 00:58:51,434
- Exactly. - You need to pick those...

1446
00:58:51,435 --> 00:58:52,975
so that they can turn yellow as they travel.

1447
00:58:54,845 --> 00:58:56,144
When you harvest them...

1448
00:58:56,145 --> 00:58:57,575
It's too late if they're already yellow.

1449
00:58:58,345 --> 00:59:00,015
Then... They're here.

1450
00:59:00,715 --> 00:59:02,314
There are bananas here and there.

1451
00:59:02,315 --> 00:59:03,655
(Green bananas hanging here and there)

1452
00:59:06,285 --> 00:59:10,255
The Philippines' local crop you'll explore in addition today...

1453
00:59:10,525 --> 00:59:13,225
is their national fruit, banana.

1454
00:59:15,995 --> 00:59:18,434
(Let's go to explore bananas.)

1455
00:59:18,435 --> 00:59:20,505
(And have fun!)

1456
00:59:22,205 --> 00:59:24,534
(The Philippines' bananas take up as much as 70 percent...)

1457
00:59:24,535 --> 00:59:26,845
(of Korea's banana imports.)

1458
00:59:27,445 --> 00:59:30,145
(This particular banana farm...)

1459
00:59:31,545 --> 00:59:34,845
(is in Calape.)

1460
00:59:36,015 --> 00:59:38,925
(Thanks to the abundant sunlight,)

1461
00:59:39,755 --> 00:59:43,455
(bananas grow all year round. It truly is a banana paradise.)

1462
00:59:43,625 --> 00:59:44,894
(Let's pause here!)

1463
00:59:44,895 --> 00:59:47,865
(How do bananas grow?)

1464
00:59:48,395 --> 00:59:50,765
(This is the flower bud of banana.)

1465
00:59:52,035 --> 00:59:53,964
(When the bract peels off,)

1466
00:59:53,965 --> 00:59:58,745
(the banana flower blooms.)

1467
00:59:59,405 --> 01:00:01,945
(When the flower with nutrients wither,)

1468
01:00:02,715 --> 01:00:06,515
(banana fruits form in that place.)

1469
01:00:07,215 --> 01:00:09,915
(The banana flower withers after yielding its nutrients.)

1470
01:00:10,455 --> 01:00:13,385
(It repeats the process...)

1471
01:00:14,255 --> 01:00:16,525
(and becomes a big banana bunch.)

1472
01:00:16,755 --> 01:00:19,065
(Before and after)

1473
01:00:19,565 --> 01:00:22,335
(Them being green doesn't mean they're not ripe.)

1474
01:00:23,235 --> 01:00:26,035
(Once they go through post-ripening after the harvest,)

1475
01:00:26,635 --> 01:00:30,675
(they become the yellow bananas we know of.)

1476
01:00:31,705 --> 01:00:34,405
(The thin skin is filled up with plump flesh.)

1477
01:00:35,945 --> 01:00:39,115
You'll harvest bananas here.

1478
01:00:39,445 --> 01:00:41,484
- We said it was an exploration. - Yes.

1479
01:00:41,485 --> 01:00:43,655
In Korea,

1480
01:00:43,855 --> 01:00:46,785
you worked for three hours in average.

1481
01:00:47,225 --> 01:00:48,624
Since today, you're just exploring,

1482
01:00:48,625 --> 01:00:49,694
(Their average working hours in Korea was 3 hours.)

1483
01:00:49,695 --> 01:00:51,494
you only have to work for one hour.

1484
01:00:51,495 --> 01:00:53,395
- Gosh. - Gosh.

1485
01:00:53,625 --> 01:00:54,765
But...

1486
01:00:55,295 --> 01:00:56,995
there is one condition.

1487
01:00:58,095 --> 01:01:00,534
But there is one condition.

1488
01:01:00,535 --> 01:01:01,834
(What condition?)

1489
01:01:01,835 --> 01:01:04,434
A local usually...

1490
01:01:04,435 --> 01:01:06,704
harvests 150 bunches of bananas in 1 hour.

1491
01:01:06,705 --> 01:01:08,104
- Did you say 150 bunches? - What?

1492
01:01:08,105 --> 01:01:09,475
(What?)

1493
01:01:09,675 --> 01:01:10,714
Go.

1494
01:01:10,715 --> 01:01:13,045
(We measured the working time ourselves.)

1495
01:01:15,655 --> 01:01:16,655
(He picked 1 bunch of bananas.)

1496
01:01:16,656 --> 01:01:17,854
(He picked 2 bunches of bananas.)

1497
01:01:17,855 --> 01:01:20,085
(He picked 3 bunches of bananas.)

1498
01:01:20,525 --> 01:01:22,624
(It took him 1 minute and 10 seconds to pick 3 bunches of bananas.)

1499
01:01:22,625 --> 01:01:26,225
(That means, in 60 minutes, he would have picked about 150 bunches.)

1500
01:01:26,525 --> 01:01:28,635
Since this is your first time,

1501
01:01:28,895 --> 01:01:30,365
you get one hour...

1502
01:01:30,935 --> 01:01:33,204
to harvest a total of 70 bunches.

1503
01:01:33,205 --> 01:01:34,265
A total of 70 bunches.

1504
01:01:34,835 --> 01:01:38,175
(The goal of their exploration: Harvesting 70 bunches in 1 hour)

1505
01:01:39,445 --> 01:01:41,504
(A team of 5 people can easily harvest 70 bunches of bananas.)

1506
01:01:41,505 --> 01:01:42,814
- That's still... - But...

1507
01:01:42,815 --> 01:01:44,474
(But what?)

1508
01:01:44,475 --> 01:01:45,885
- There's another "but." - Go ahead.

1509
01:01:45,945 --> 01:01:48,144
This is supposed to be...

1510
01:01:48,145 --> 01:01:51,155
a fun extra exploration of local crops, right?

1511
01:01:51,825 --> 01:01:54,085
- So we're giving you an option. - Okay.

1512
01:01:54,725 --> 01:01:55,794
Come on out.

1513
01:01:55,795 --> 01:01:56,925
- What's going on? - What?

1514
01:01:57,555 --> 01:01:58,695
Come on out.

1515
01:01:59,065 --> 01:02:00,095
- What did she say? - What?

1516
01:02:01,935 --> 01:02:03,035
What's coming out?

1517
01:02:04,665 --> 01:02:06,035
Maybe there's another guest.

1518
01:02:06,765 --> 01:02:07,805
Is it Hwang Ga Ram?

1519
01:02:10,505 --> 01:02:12,845
(Hwang Ga Ram is at the banana farm?)

1520
01:02:17,775 --> 01:02:18,815
What?

1521
01:02:18,985 --> 01:02:20,915
What is that? "Commandments of Exploration?"

1522
01:02:24,715 --> 01:02:29,355
(A group of staff members files in one after another.)

1523
01:02:30,655 --> 01:02:32,264
(And printed on their T-shirts are...)

1524
01:02:32,265 --> 01:02:34,595
(suspicious-looking words.)

1525
01:02:34,665 --> 01:02:35,835
Can you read it out loud?

1526
01:02:36,295 --> 01:02:37,335
Together?

1527
01:02:38,035 --> 01:02:39,134
(The Five Commandments of Fun Additional Exploration)

1528
01:02:39,135 --> 01:02:41,564
- Number one. No acting out. - No acting out.

1529
01:02:41,565 --> 01:02:43,174
- No sighing. - No sighing.

1530
01:02:43,175 --> 01:02:45,804
- No blaming others. - No blaming others.

1531
01:02:45,805 --> 01:02:48,244
- No frowning. - No frowning.

1532
01:02:48,245 --> 01:02:50,215
- No grumbling. - No grumbling.

1533
01:02:50,375 --> 01:02:51,544
What is that?

1534
01:02:51,545 --> 01:02:55,314
When did we ever act out?

1535
01:02:55,315 --> 01:02:58,355
- You must have acted out a lot. - "No blaming others."

1536
01:02:58,555 --> 01:03:01,524
- Gosh. - So what's going to happen is...

1537
01:03:01,525 --> 01:03:03,754
a staff member will be assigned...

1538
01:03:03,755 --> 01:03:05,725
to keep an eye on each of you.

1539
01:03:06,765 --> 01:03:09,365
(Keep an eye on what?)

1540
01:03:09,595 --> 01:03:12,904
So whenever you break 1 of the 5 commandments,

1541
01:03:12,905 --> 01:03:13,965
- Yes. - Yes.

1542
01:03:14,565 --> 01:03:17,104
we will take away one bunch out of the bunches you harvested.

1543
01:03:17,105 --> 01:03:18,645
(A bunch will be deducted from the harvested bananas each time.)

1544
01:03:19,875 --> 01:03:22,115
- You'll take one bunch? - Goodness, really?

1545
01:03:22,375 --> 01:03:23,375
(An additional exploration of local crops)

1546
01:03:23,376 --> 01:03:25,075
(A fun additional exploration of local crops)

1547
01:03:25,585 --> 01:03:27,744
(The monitors will each be carrying a whistle.)

1548
01:03:27,745 --> 01:03:28,814
(Record keeper, monitor)

1549
01:03:28,815 --> 01:03:30,385
Yum Jung Ah, one count of acting out.

1550
01:03:31,415 --> 01:03:34,255
(Their violations will be recorded on the monitoring list,)

1551
01:03:34,525 --> 01:03:35,924
(and one bunch will be deducted...)

1552
01:03:35,925 --> 01:03:37,854
(from the harvested bananas.)

1553
01:03:37,855 --> 01:03:39,594
Let's say you harvested 70 bunches within 1 hour.

1554
01:03:39,595 --> 01:03:42,834
If the deducted amount adds up and you only end up with 60 bunches,

1555
01:03:42,835 --> 01:03:45,205
you must harvest ten more bunches even after the hour is up.

1556
01:03:45,905 --> 01:03:47,264
(They must make up for the 10 bunches to be done.)

1557
01:03:47,265 --> 01:03:49,505
So we can't leave until we have 70 bunches.

1558
01:03:51,035 --> 01:03:53,675
(They have to leave within 1 hour...)

1559
01:03:54,105 --> 01:03:57,245
(to make it to their five-star foot massage on time.)

1560
01:03:57,475 --> 01:03:59,685
Can we begin now, if we haven't already?

1561
01:04:01,815 --> 01:04:03,884
They're so high up. How do we harvest these?

1562
01:04:03,885 --> 01:04:05,685
Do we go on top of something?

1563
01:04:06,055 --> 01:04:09,554
- Right. We need to be on something. - But we can't.

1564
01:04:09,555 --> 01:04:11,555
(Will they be able to have fun while harvesting these?)

1565
01:04:12,365 --> 01:04:14,394
(They had fun getting changed.)

1566
01:04:14,395 --> 01:04:16,664
- But the bananas... - No acting out.

1567
01:04:16,665 --> 01:04:17,694
That's right.

1568
01:04:17,695 --> 01:04:19,735
(Laughing)

1569
01:04:19,935 --> 01:04:23,204
Let's hurry up and do this. Let's get harvesting.

1570
01:04:23,205 --> 01:04:24,674
(Wait.)

1571
01:04:24,675 --> 01:04:25,905
I wasn't acting out.

1572
01:04:26,875 --> 01:04:28,144
- She's so excited to begin. - I was rushing us.

1573
01:04:28,145 --> 01:04:29,145
