(Smiling all the time to secure the bananas)

1837
01:15:43,755 --> 01:15:44,755
Again.

1838
01:15:45,485 --> 01:15:46,924
Again. Let's do this, Kim Hye Yoon.

1839
01:15:46,925 --> 01:15:48,285
(I'm really not tired at all.)

1840
01:15:48,955 --> 01:15:51,355
Let's all cheer up at work.

1841
01:15:52,155 --> 01:15:53,395
Let's smile and work.

1842
01:15:55,765 --> 01:15:57,834
That one looks pretty big.

1843
01:15:57,835 --> 01:15:58,835
(While the youngest is acting passionately,)

1844
01:15:58,836 --> 01:16:01,504
(here is the genuinely lunatic guy.)

1845
01:16:01,505 --> 01:16:02,505
(Amazed)

1846
01:16:05,375 --> 01:16:06,744
(Surprised)

1847
01:16:06,745 --> 01:16:08,974
Hurrah! It's the biggest.

1848
01:16:08,975 --> 01:16:11,045
(Happy)

1849
01:16:11,145 --> 01:16:13,845
I can do this!

1850
01:16:15,315 --> 01:16:17,315
Let's go!

1851
01:16:17,815 --> 01:16:21,825
I think Dex gets energized when he comes to places like this.

1852
01:16:22,385 --> 01:16:24,294
He hasn't broken a single commandment,

1853
01:16:24,295 --> 01:16:25,295
not even a sigh.

1854
01:16:25,695 --> 01:16:27,294
(One hit,)

1855
01:16:27,295 --> 01:16:29,125
(one kill)

1856
01:16:29,795 --> 01:16:34,535
(The energizer doesn't get tired.)

1857
01:16:34,935 --> 01:16:38,635
(He is improving as he goes.)

1858
01:16:39,975 --> 01:16:42,045
(Full of vigor)

1859
01:16:42,175 --> 01:16:43,175
It's fun.

1860
01:16:44,015 --> 01:16:45,015
It's fun.

1861
01:16:45,016 --> 01:16:46,884
(An explosion of dopamine)

1862
01:16:46,885 --> 01:16:49,315
I was supposed to work out today.

1863
01:16:49,615 --> 01:16:51,355
I get to make up for it with this. Isn't that nice?

1864
01:16:55,255 --> 01:16:56,754
Let's go find another one.

1865
01:16:56,755 --> 01:16:57,755
(True madness)

1866
01:16:58,055 --> 01:16:59,495
Another good banana bundle.

1867
01:16:59,595 --> 01:17:01,164
Let's find top-tier bananas.

1868
01:17:01,165 --> 01:17:02,595
(Dex went on a banana hunt again.)

1869
01:17:02,965 --> 01:17:05,835
(20 minutes since the exploration started)

1870
01:17:06,235 --> 01:17:07,734
(Leader Yum is splitting the bananas...)

1871
01:17:07,735 --> 01:17:11,075
(without even straightening her back once.)

1872
01:17:12,905 --> 01:17:13,905
Here you go.

1873
01:17:13,906 --> 01:17:17,175
(It isn't easy to separate them due to the tough stem.)

1874
01:17:17,575 --> 01:17:22,045
(Still, she's doing her best.)

1875
01:17:22,415 --> 01:17:23,784
Jung Ah, I brought this too.

1876
01:17:23,785 --> 01:17:24,885
Thank you.

1877
01:17:26,025 --> 01:17:27,385
Jung Ah, I'll put this here.

1878
01:17:27,855 --> 01:17:28,855
Okay.

1879
01:17:30,225 --> 01:17:32,124
- Fifteen. - Fifteen.

1880
01:17:32,125 --> 01:17:33,825
- I'll go down there. - Thank you.

1881
01:17:34,025 --> 01:17:35,025
(4 more bananas)

1882
01:17:36,395 --> 01:17:38,865
(Her work comes in nonstop.)

1883
01:17:39,405 --> 01:17:40,464
Jung Ah, there's more.

1884
01:17:40,465 --> 01:17:41,634
(He delivers another one on top of it.)

1885
01:17:41,635 --> 01:17:42,735
Thank you.

1886
01:17:43,275 --> 01:17:44,804
Is it too much work? Should I send them somewhere else?

1887
01:17:44,805 --> 01:17:46,605
No, give me all of them.

1888
01:17:48,475 --> 01:17:51,075
You're not angry, are you?

1889
01:17:52,345 --> 01:17:54,515
(What do you mean, angry?)

1890
01:17:54,815 --> 01:17:56,685
(Laughing)

1891
01:17:57,315 --> 01:17:59,454
Everyone is smiling on this worksite.

1892
01:17:59,455 --> 01:18:00,485
(Exploring bananas is so much fun.)

1893
01:18:00,855 --> 01:18:04,425
(She cuts and cuts, but so much work is piled up.)

1894
01:18:06,665 --> 01:18:11,235
(She won't be able to get off work in 1 hour at this rate.)

1895
01:18:11,765 --> 01:18:13,705
(In that case...)

1896
01:18:14,435 --> 01:18:18,735
(Shall I speed up?)

1897
01:18:19,035 --> 01:18:22,104
(She cuts...)

1898
01:18:22,105 --> 01:18:23,475
(and cuts.)

1899
01:18:24,015 --> 01:18:26,114
(Accurate timing...)

1900
01:18:26,115 --> 01:18:28,215
(and perfect aim)

1901
01:18:28,715 --> 01:18:30,084
(She fills up one basket in an instant.)

1902
01:18:30,085 --> 01:18:31,485
You're really good at it, Jung Ah.

1903
01:18:31,785 --> 01:18:34,955
We must hurry up if we want to do everything planned for today.

1904
01:18:36,125 --> 01:18:39,825
(She's almost in a trance.)

1905
01:18:40,065 --> 01:18:42,294
Step back. I can cut it down at once.

1906
01:18:42,295 --> 01:18:43,295
(She even gives it a go at harvesting.)

1907
01:18:43,895 --> 01:18:48,005
(Very determined to get off work on time)

1908
01:18:48,535 --> 01:18:49,904
- You're doing great. - It's falling.

1909
01:18:49,905 --> 01:18:51,275
It's falling.

1910
01:18:52,535 --> 01:18:55,345
(She harvests it quickly.)

1911
01:18:55,675 --> 01:18:57,074
(She's good.)

1912
01:18:57,075 --> 01:18:58,075
Here.

1913
01:18:58,915 --> 01:19:00,045
Isn't it fun?

1914
01:19:00,985 --> 01:19:02,614
It isn't fun.

1915
01:19:02,615 --> 01:19:03,685
(She's just desperate to get off work.)

1916
01:19:04,015 --> 01:19:07,585
(Can she get off work on time?)

1917
01:19:07,985 --> 01:19:10,355
(Meanwhile)

1918
01:19:12,655 --> 01:19:15,825
(Jun Myun is exceptionally quiet today.)

1919
01:19:16,535 --> 01:19:18,665
Are you not saying anything in case you end up sighing?

1920
01:19:18,765 --> 01:19:20,135
That's not the case.

1921
01:19:21,365 --> 01:19:23,905
I'm worried I'll sigh and get the banana count deducted.

1922
01:19:24,305 --> 01:19:25,505
There's that.

1923
01:19:26,645 --> 01:19:30,345
(I reflect on my past actions.)

1924
01:19:31,051 --> 01:19:32,250
Yes.

1925
01:19:32,275 --> 01:19:34,415
(Jun Myun works twice as hard to make up for the loss.)

1926
01:19:34,715 --> 01:19:36,414
- Jun Myun, would you like to try? - Yes.

1927
01:19:36,415 --> 01:19:37,755
- I want to try. - Come with me.

1928
01:19:38,085 --> 01:19:39,085
This way, please.

1929
01:19:39,855 --> 01:19:41,554
It kind of helps to relieve stress.

1930
01:19:41,555 --> 01:19:42,555
- Really? - Yes.
(Jun Myun gives it a go at harvesting the fruit too.)

1931
01:19:43,995 --> 01:19:45,595
- Into a V-shape? - Yes.

1932
01:19:48,124 --> 01:19:49,324
(Surprised)

1933
01:19:49,425 --> 01:19:50,435
Above it.

1934
01:19:50,735 --> 01:19:52,194
Do I cut it into a V-shape?

1935
01:19:52,195 --> 01:19:53,805
You can do that, or you can just keep hitting it.

1936
01:19:53,905 --> 01:19:54,965
As if you're mincing it.

1937
01:19:55,435 --> 01:19:57,205
Darn it.

1938
01:19:59,840 --> 01:20:00,840
(Whistle)

1939
01:20:01,145 --> 01:20:02,844
Park Jun Myun, one "darn it!"

1940
01:20:02,845 --> 01:20:06,845
(She gets a warning as soon as she changes her task.)

1941
01:20:07,085 --> 01:20:08,314
When you say "darn it,"

1942
01:20:08,315 --> 01:20:10,485
- say "I want a darn cool drink." - It's darn cool.

1943
01:20:10,885 --> 01:20:12,685
- It's darn cool. - It's darn cool.

1944
01:20:12,785 --> 01:20:14,555
Gosh, it's so darn cool!

1945
01:20:17,225 --> 01:20:18,225
Good.

1946
01:20:18,226 --> 01:20:19,795
(She collects herself and gives it a go again.)

1947
01:20:19,865 --> 01:20:22,935
(Mouth clenched shut)

1948
01:20:22,965 --> 01:20:24,134
A bit more.

1949
01:20:24,135 --> 01:20:26,604
(It looks like it'll fall if she chops a bit more.)

1950
01:20:26,605 --> 01:20:28,204
- Darn it. - A bit more.

1951
01:20:28,205 --> 01:20:29,574
(She loses another point right away.)

1952
01:20:29,575 --> 01:20:31,134
Park Jun Myun, one "darn it!"

1953
01:20:31,135 --> 01:20:32,904
Wait a moment. That was a shout.

1954
01:20:32,905 --> 01:20:34,104
It's a shout.

1955
01:20:34,105 --> 01:20:35,674
No, I heard it clearly.

1956
01:20:35,675 --> 01:20:36,715
(Making another pathetic excuse)

1957
01:20:36,915 --> 01:20:38,614
Hey! See, it's a shout.

1958
01:20:38,615 --> 01:20:39,745
Yes, that's fine.

1959
01:20:40,215 --> 01:20:41,215
(Shouting)

1960
01:20:41,845 --> 01:20:44,784
(She pulls herself together and tries again.)

1961
01:20:44,785 --> 01:20:45,785
Darn it.

1962
01:20:46,625 --> 01:20:47,625
- Darn it. - No!

1963
01:20:48,385 --> 01:20:50,225
(Looking around)

1964
01:20:50,655 --> 01:20:52,895
(He's about to blow the whistle.)

1965
01:20:53,425 --> 01:20:54,724
What's the matter with you?

1966
01:20:54,725 --> 01:20:56,535
Wait.

1967
01:20:56,865 --> 01:20:58,035
Just let it slide this once.

1968
01:20:58,235 --> 01:21:00,435
- This once. - She's not young, you know.

1969
01:21:00,765 --> 01:21:02,034
What did you say?

1970
01:21:02,035 --> 01:21:04,335
That's even more offensive. You know what I mean?

1971
01:21:04,475 --> 01:21:05,974
A meddling sister-in-law is more annoying.

1972
01:21:05,975 --> 01:21:06,975
Let's laugh.

1973
01:21:07,775 --> 01:21:10,315
(Jun Myun isn't angry at all.)

1974
01:21:10,775 --> 01:21:13,515
This is the fifth time Jun Myun grumbled.

1975
01:21:14,185 --> 01:21:15,185
(Whistle)

1976
01:21:15,186 --> 01:21:16,585
Lee Si Eon, one count of blaming others.

1977
01:21:17,055 --> 01:21:18,684
(You have to watch what you say at all times.)

1978
01:21:18,685 --> 01:21:19,755
Hey!

1979
01:21:21,985 --> 01:21:23,925
- Let's count how many we got. - Okay.

1980
01:21:24,455 --> 01:21:25,695
We have to count them now.

1981
01:21:26,195 --> 01:21:29,094
One, two, three, four.

1982
01:21:29,095 --> 01:21:30,294
- Excuse me. - That's five.

1983
01:21:30,295 --> 01:21:31,894
(The siblings are gathered with the bananas they each harvested.)

1984
01:21:31,895 --> 01:21:32,895
That's six.

1985
01:21:33,305 --> 01:21:34,335
That's eight.

1986
01:21:35,165 --> 01:21:36,165
That's nine.

1987
01:21:36,675 --> 01:21:37,735
We have ten.

1988
01:21:38,005 --> 01:21:40,474
It's 1, 2, 3, 4, 5.

1989
01:21:40,475 --> 01:21:41,575
We have 15.

1990
01:21:42,305 --> 01:21:45,415
That's 16, 17, 18.

1991
01:21:46,115 --> 01:21:47,145
And 19.

1992
01:21:47,815 --> 01:21:48,844
We have 29.

1993
01:21:48,845 --> 01:21:50,115
(After counting about half of their harvest, he's already at 29.)

1994
01:21:50,555 --> 01:21:53,155
(That's a lot.)

1995
01:21:53,585 --> 01:21:55,825
We might not have enough.

1996
01:21:56,425 --> 01:21:57,924
We got a lot deducted.

1997
01:21:57,925 --> 01:21:59,795
I'm thinking we got about ten deducted.

1998
01:21:59,925 --> 01:22:01,165
It's probably more than ten.

1999
01:22:01,325 --> 01:22:02,695
- More than ten? - Yes.

2000
01:22:03,595 --> 01:22:05,865
I should check which plants have bananas, just in case.

2001
01:22:06,505 --> 01:22:08,865
We might need at least ten more.

2002
01:22:09,465 --> 01:22:11,474
Right, Dex? We should harvest at least a few more.

2003
01:22:11,475 --> 01:22:12,475
Yes.

2004
01:22:12,705 --> 01:22:14,445
First, let's see how many you have so far.

2005
01:22:15,945 --> 01:22:16,974
Was that you acting out?

2006
01:22:16,975 --> 01:22:18,474
(Did you just act out?)

2007
01:22:18,475 --> 01:22:20,185
"First, let's see how many you have so far."

2008
01:22:20,815 --> 01:22:22,184
Was that you blaming me?

2009
01:22:22,185 --> 01:22:23,255
It was me mimicking you.

2010
01:22:23,785 --> 01:22:24,785
That's seven.

2011
01:22:24,786 --> 01:22:26,455
Can we deduct from the production staff?

2012
01:22:26,555 --> 01:22:28,324
For every time you act out, we get one extra bunch.

2013
01:22:28,325 --> 01:22:29,455
(For every time you act out, we get 1 extra bunch.)

2014
01:22:29,895 --> 01:22:33,165
(We're all smiling as we work.)

2015
01:22:33,595 --> 01:22:37,965
(Dex counts the rest of their harvest.)

2016
01:22:38,195 --> 01:22:39,335
How many do we have right now?

2017
01:22:39,865 --> 01:22:41,165
We have 67 bunches.

2018
01:22:41,665 --> 01:22:43,535
We have 67 bunches including this one.

2019
01:22:43,575 --> 01:22:45,204
- What's our goal again? - It's 70.

2020
01:22:45,205 --> 01:22:46,275
It's 70 bunches?

2021
01:22:47,575 --> 01:22:49,644
(The deciding factor of when they get to leave work)

2022
01:22:49,645 --> 01:22:52,715
(The number of warnings they got for breaking the 5 commandments)

2023
01:22:53,315 --> 01:22:57,254
(How many times did they break them?)

2024
01:22:57,255 --> 01:22:59,514
This is the midway count.

2025
01:22:59,515 --> 01:23:00,625
(Their current cumulative count is revealed.)

2026
01:23:00,955 --> 01:23:03,095
Jung Ah, three warnings.

2027
01:23:03,855 --> 01:23:05,725
Hye Yoon, two warnings.

2028
01:23:06,995 --> 01:23:08,865
Si Eon, three warnings.

2029
01:23:10,135 --> 01:23:12,595
- I probably don't have any. - Dex, zero warnings.

2030
01:23:14,005 --> 01:23:16,635
(They currently have 8 deductions.)

2031
01:23:17,235 --> 01:23:20,145
(It's up to Jun Myun now.)

2032
01:23:20,575 --> 01:23:22,575
Jun Myun, five warnings.

2033
01:23:22,775 --> 01:23:25,345
(Shocked)

2034
01:23:25,615 --> 01:23:27,315
I got five warnings?

2035
01:23:27,445 --> 01:23:28,445
Gosh.

2036
01:23:28,446 --> 01:23:30,014
(She is in denial.)

2037
01:23:30,015 --> 01:23:31,584
(Current cumulative warning count)

2038
01:23:31,585 --> 01:23:34,054
(Jung Ah: 3, Hye Yoon: 2, Si Eon: 3, Dex: 0, Jun Myun: 5)

2039
01:23:34,055 --> 01:23:36,394
You have a total of 13 warnings.

2040
01:23:36,395 --> 01:23:38,795
- So we have to add 13, right? - Yes.

2041
01:23:39,355 --> 01:23:41,494
We have 67 here, right now.

2042
01:23:41,495 --> 01:23:42,595
We need a total of 83.

2043
01:23:43,235 --> 01:23:46,805
As long as we stay silent, the goal is 83.

2044
01:23:47,405 --> 01:23:48,405
(Sighing)

2045
01:23:48,406 --> 01:23:51,075
(Extremely worried)

2046
01:23:51,575 --> 01:23:53,874
(There are 20 minutes remaining.)

2047
01:23:53,875 --> 01:23:56,245
(They have to harvest at least 16 bunches in that time!)

2048
01:23:56,675 --> 01:23:59,515
(They're taking drastic measures to leave work on time.)

2049
01:23:59,785 --> 01:24:01,015
Starting now,

2050
01:24:01,645 --> 01:24:03,215
let's just not speak.

2051
01:24:03,955 --> 01:24:06,455
Let's not even breathe loudly.

2052
01:24:07,055 --> 01:24:09,995
(Those who wish to leave work...)

2053
01:24:10,555 --> 01:24:12,995
(must keep their mouths shut!)

2054
01:24:13,325 --> 01:24:15,464
- No blaming others. - No blaming others.

2055
01:24:15,465 --> 01:24:16,635
No blaming others.

2056
01:24:16,735 --> 01:24:18,195
- Where are we going to... - Jung Ah, smile.

2057
01:24:18,635 --> 01:24:20,105
Where are we going to gather the bananas?

2058
01:24:20,565 --> 01:24:22,004
(To leave work on time,)

2059
01:24:22,005 --> 01:24:23,474
(the siblings join forces.)

2060
01:24:23,475 --> 01:24:24,904
- This is a big one. - Amazing.

2061
01:24:24,905 --> 01:24:26,075
This one's great.

2062
01:24:26,205 --> 01:24:27,405
We need as many bunches as we can get.

2063
01:24:28,345 --> 01:24:29,375
Gosh.

2064
01:24:29,545 --> 01:24:30,545
(Whistle)

2065
01:24:30,745 --> 01:24:32,375
Park Jun Myun, one count of grumbling.

2066
01:24:32,675 --> 01:24:33,745
You're saying...

2067
01:24:34,545 --> 01:24:35,884
(With 1 more added, their goal is now 84 bunches.)

2068
01:24:35,885 --> 01:24:37,254
I just grumbled?

2069
01:24:37,255 --> 01:24:39,514
(With 1 more added, their goal is now 84 bunches.)

2070
01:24:39,515 --> 01:24:40,985
Lee Si Eon, one count of blaming others.

2071
01:24:41,655 --> 01:24:43,525
Kim Hye Yoon, one count of complaining.

2072
01:24:44,125 --> 01:24:45,955
Yum Jung Ah, one count of sighing.

2073
01:24:46,095 --> 01:24:47,895
Why do we keep getting deductions?

2074
01:24:50,095 --> 01:24:51,194
That's understandable.

2075
01:24:51,195 --> 01:24:52,235
(A sudden change in attitude)

2076
01:24:52,295 --> 01:24:53,605
Put down your whistle.

2077
01:24:53,665 --> 01:24:55,034
I think it's understandable.

2078
01:24:55,035 --> 01:24:56,205
I'm not blaming anyone.

2079
01:24:56,735 --> 01:24:58,805
(And...)

2080
01:24:59,405 --> 01:25:01,145
- Yes? - One count of frowning.

2081
01:25:01,675 --> 01:25:03,214
(Their harvest goal is 87 bunches.)

2082
01:25:03,215 --> 01:25:05,145
(With 1 more added, their harvest goal is 88 bunches.)

2083
01:25:05,475 --> 01:25:06,585
Jun Myun.

2084
01:25:07,315 --> 01:25:08,415
You're doing great.

2085
01:25:08,585 --> 01:25:10,355
(Laughing)

2086
01:25:10,785 --> 01:25:12,214
I almost blamed you.

2087
01:25:12,215 --> 01:25:14,185
(That was a close call.)

2088
01:25:14,655 --> 01:25:17,894
(Now they're really almost out of time.)

2089
01:25:17,895 --> 01:25:19,595
- All right, Byung Man. - Smile!

2090
01:25:20,225 --> 01:25:21,425
You got this, Byung Man!

2091
01:25:22,287 --> 01:25:23,427
I'm so happy!

2092
01:25:24,135 --> 01:25:25,764
(Gosh)

2093
01:25:25,765 --> 01:25:27,464
It feels great when this falls over.

2094
01:25:27,465 --> 01:25:28,465
- Really? - Yes.

2095
01:25:28,466 --> 01:25:29,535
- This way. - Okay.

2096
01:25:29,805 --> 01:25:31,375
Okay. That's holding it up.

2097
01:25:32,035 --> 01:25:33,035
It's going down.

2098
01:25:34,575 --> 01:25:37,315
(Hye Yoon successfully harvested a cluster.)

2099
01:25:37,545 --> 01:25:39,614
- I got chills. - Nice.

2100
01:25:39,615 --> 01:25:40,645
Si Eon!

