2358
01:35:47,015 --> 01:35:48,054
(Feeling anxious)

2359
01:35:48,055 --> 01:35:49,554
Should we just give it a try with the first one?

2360
01:35:49,555 --> 01:35:50,895
- We'll be making several of them. - Let's try it with the first one.

2361
01:35:51,825 --> 01:35:56,224
(They start cooking the first pancake.)

2362
01:35:56,225 --> 01:35:57,495
Isn't this a kimchi jeon?

2363
01:35:57,848 --> 01:35:58,742
Si Eon?

2364
01:35:58,965 --> 01:35:59,965
It's the pancake jeon.

2365
01:36:00,395 --> 01:36:02,435
- Think of it as the banana jeon. - Pancake jeon?

2366
01:36:03,005 --> 01:36:04,005
Korean-style.
(Korean banana jeon?)

2367
01:36:05,006 --> 01:36:06,634
Hey, it smells good, doesn't it?

2368
01:36:06,635 --> 01:36:08,105
Right.

2369
01:36:08,205 --> 01:36:09,475
Would you like to try and flip it?

2370
01:36:10,715 --> 01:36:12,444
The oil might splatter. You have to be careful.

2371
01:36:12,445 --> 01:36:13,445
(It's time for Chef Hye Yoon to show her skills.)

2372
01:36:13,446 --> 01:36:14,545
You have to be careful.

2373
01:36:15,285 --> 01:36:17,815
(Focused)

2374
01:36:22,025 --> 01:36:23,025
Gosh.

2375
01:36:27,595 --> 01:36:30,194
(Dark)

2376
01:36:30,195 --> 01:36:32,595
Gosh. What happened?

2377
01:36:33,135 --> 01:36:34,964
- What is this? It's burnt! - That was why I left three.

2378
01:36:34,965 --> 01:36:36,264
No. It didn't get burnt.

2379
01:36:36,265 --> 01:36:37,675
It's crunchy on the outside and soft on the inside.

2380
01:36:38,205 --> 01:36:39,205
Here!

2381
01:36:39,435 --> 01:36:42,004
(Isn't it burnt on the outside and uncooked in the inside?)

2382
01:36:42,005 --> 01:36:43,644
- Don't look over here. - Is this the plate?

2383
01:36:43,645 --> 01:36:44,874
- The pancake plate? - Right.

2384
01:36:44,875 --> 01:36:46,544
- It's too burnt! - I'll bring the bananas.

2385
01:36:46,545 --> 01:36:47,884
It isn't burnt.

2386
01:36:47,885 --> 01:36:50,344
- It's too burnt, Hye Yoon. - They have a lot of...

2387
01:36:50,345 --> 01:36:51,985
burnt food here.

2388
01:36:53,785 --> 01:36:54,854
I like burnt food.

2389
01:36:54,855 --> 01:36:55,885
(Was this grilled?)

2390
01:36:56,655 --> 01:36:59,055
(Let's give it a try.)

2391
01:37:04,235 --> 01:37:07,135
Hey, Hye Yoon, give it a try. I just tried it.

2392
01:37:07,665 --> 01:37:11,804
(How does it taste?)

2393
01:37:11,805 --> 01:37:12,934
(What?)

2394
01:37:12,935 --> 01:37:14,074
It's good, isn't it?

2395
01:37:14,075 --> 01:37:15,375
What? Why is it so good?

2396
01:37:15,605 --> 01:37:16,975
Right? It's good, isn't it?

2397
01:37:17,345 --> 01:37:19,614
- It's really good. - Surprisingly, it's really good.

2398
01:37:19,615 --> 01:37:20,815
- Right. - Why is it good?

2399
01:37:21,245 --> 01:37:22,314
It's so good.

2400
01:37:22,315 --> 01:37:24,615
(She gets boosted with confidence by the surprising taste...)

2401
01:37:25,055 --> 01:37:28,325
(and carries on with the dish.)

2402
01:37:28,485 --> 01:37:31,825
(The leftover bananas get sliced.)

2403
01:37:31,955 --> 01:37:33,395
How does this look?

2404
01:37:33,595 --> 01:37:34,894
- Just like this. - That's nice.

2405
01:37:34,895 --> 01:37:35,895
- And another one on top. - Right.

2406
01:37:36,065 --> 01:37:38,095
It will be great with some syrup.

2407
01:37:38,735 --> 01:37:39,895
That's a great idea.

2408
01:37:40,265 --> 01:37:41,535
Whatever.

2409
01:37:42,205 --> 01:37:43,805
I think it's ready now.

2410
01:37:44,175 --> 01:37:45,175
(It's topped with some honey.)

2411
01:37:45,176 --> 01:37:46,934
It's ready now.

2412
01:37:46,935 --> 01:37:47,945
(It's topped with some honey.)

2413
01:37:48,105 --> 01:37:49,774
The tteokbokki is ready.

2414
01:37:49,775 --> 01:37:51,545
(The rabokki is ready right on time as well.)

2415
01:37:52,345 --> 01:37:54,485
(Also, the middle-end meal coupon's...)

2416
01:37:54,785 --> 01:37:58,415
(barbecue that Mark recommended is prepared as well.)

2417
01:37:58,785 --> 01:38:01,284
(After being cooked directly on a charcoal grill,)

2418
01:38:01,285 --> 01:38:04,525
(the chicken and pork have become crunchy outside, and soft inside.)

2419
01:38:04,725 --> 01:38:06,054
Quickly get this prepared, Jun Myun!

2420
01:38:06,055 --> 01:38:07,694
- What is it? - The chicken.

2421
01:38:07,695 --> 01:38:09,165
(Your food delivery is here.)

2422
01:38:09,525 --> 01:38:11,494
Gosh, it looks amazing.

2423
01:38:11,495 --> 01:38:12,495
(Smoky local barbecue)

2424
01:38:12,496 --> 01:38:13,535
Gosh!

2425
01:38:13,835 --> 01:38:15,204
The tteokbokki smells great!

2426
01:38:15,205 --> 01:38:16,634
Gosh, smell this.

2427
01:38:16,635 --> 01:38:18,204
- It smells amazing. - Tteokbokki in the Philippines!

2428
01:38:18,205 --> 01:38:20,304
- How is it? - It looks great! You did well.

2429
01:38:20,305 --> 01:38:21,774
- It looks nice, doesn't it? - It looks great.

2430
01:38:21,775 --> 01:38:26,215
- Thank you for the meal. - Thank you for the meal.

2431
01:38:26,475 --> 01:38:27,484
My ramyeon.

2432
01:38:27,485 --> 01:38:30,485
(It's time to fill their hungry stomachs.)

2433
01:38:30,885 --> 01:38:32,385
It's really good. I already tried it.

2434
01:38:32,615 --> 01:38:33,854
Gosh, thank you.

2435
01:38:33,855 --> 01:38:34,885
It was well-cooked.

2436
01:38:35,725 --> 01:38:38,225
(She takes a bite of the barbecue first.)

2437
01:38:38,325 --> 01:38:40,154
- They say this is a great place. - Gosh, it's good.

2438
01:38:40,155 --> 01:38:41,494
(Satisfied)

2439
01:38:41,495 --> 01:38:43,464
It has the scent of the Philippines.

2440
01:38:43,465 --> 01:38:44,835
- It's nice and salty. - It's nice and salty.

2441
01:38:45,065 --> 01:38:47,705
(Full of meat juice)

2442
01:38:48,605 --> 01:38:50,434
(Hye Yoon eats...)

2443
01:38:50,435 --> 01:38:52,975
(and eats again.)

2444
01:38:53,135 --> 01:38:54,574
(Hye Yoon loves it.)

2445
01:38:54,575 --> 01:38:55,775
The chicken is so good.

2446
01:38:56,905 --> 01:38:59,215
(Finding her to be cute)

2447
01:39:00,415 --> 01:39:04,715
(How does Jung Ah and Dex's rabokki taste?)

2448
01:39:05,485 --> 01:39:07,385
- The rabokki is so good, Jung Ah. - Pork belly.

2449
01:39:07,485 --> 01:39:08,485
- Thank you. - Jin Young made it.

2450
01:39:08,486 --> 01:39:10,385
I'm serious. Out of all the rabokkis I've tried,

2451
01:39:10,525 --> 01:39:11,794
this is the best.

2452
01:39:11,795 --> 01:39:12,924
- Really? - Yes.

2453
01:39:12,925 --> 01:39:15,265
- Si Eon is full of compliments. - It's so good.

2454
01:39:16,195 --> 01:39:17,334
The rabokki is amazing.

2455
01:39:17,335 --> 01:39:18,665
(It's a legendary taste.)

2456
01:39:18,895 --> 01:39:19,965
Jin Young made it.

2457
01:39:21,065 --> 01:39:23,005
- Jung Ah seasoned it so well. - Right.

2458
01:39:23,465 --> 01:39:24,675
- It's so good. - Right.

2459
01:39:25,205 --> 01:39:26,205
It's so good.

2460
01:39:26,206 --> 01:39:28,104
(A rush of compliments flows by.)

2461
01:39:28,105 --> 01:39:29,805
You're not touching the pancake, Jun Myun.

2462
01:39:30,845 --> 01:39:31,914
Well...

2463
01:39:31,915 --> 01:39:34,044
(The pancake wasn't touched.)

2464
01:39:34,045 --> 01:39:35,184
Well, I wanted to end the meal...

2465
01:39:35,185 --> 01:39:36,344
- with it. - I see.

2466
01:39:36,345 --> 01:39:38,085
I finished the one I got.

2467
01:39:42,025 --> 01:39:43,025
I ate it.

2468
01:39:46,595 --> 01:39:47,995
It's good, isn't it?

2469
01:39:48,465 --> 01:39:49,765
Didn't you leave it as well?

2470
01:39:49,825 --> 01:39:51,135
I didn't have a single bite of it.

2471
01:39:51,935 --> 01:39:53,135
I only had it when we tasted it earlier.

2472
01:39:53,295 --> 01:39:54,335
I'll give it a try.

2473
01:39:54,465 --> 01:39:55,504
A knife isn't needed.

2474
01:39:55,505 --> 01:39:58,205
(Food expert Jun Myun will give a review.)

2475
01:39:59,509 --> 01:40:01,074
She's a food expert.

2476
01:40:01,075 --> 01:40:03,275
(What will she think?)

2477
01:40:03,575 --> 01:40:04,439
It's good.

2478
01:40:06,815 --> 01:40:07,845
We'll have to accept it.

2479
01:40:08,085 --> 01:40:09,845
- With a bit of disappointment. - It's good.

2480
01:40:10,185 --> 01:40:11,654
It's actually good.

2481
01:40:11,655 --> 01:40:12,884
- Right? - I'll place it here.

2482
01:40:12,885 --> 01:40:13,985
Have some confidence!

2483
01:40:14,185 --> 01:40:16,524
(Stay strong, Pancake!)

2484
01:40:16,525 --> 01:40:18,695
The cinnamon scent is great with the bananas.

2485
01:40:19,725 --> 01:40:21,894
- We never put in cinnamon. - Really?

2486
01:40:21,895 --> 01:40:23,694
I don't know where it's from.

2487
01:40:23,695 --> 01:40:24,865
The cinnamon is great, isn't it?

2488
01:40:25,665 --> 01:40:28,404
I felt this while making the pancakes with him.

2489
01:40:28,405 --> 01:40:31,005
I think he'll become a great dad.

2490
01:40:31,135 --> 01:40:32,205
Thank you.

2491
01:40:33,105 --> 01:40:34,374
Did you two have perfect teamwork?

2492
01:40:34,375 --> 01:40:37,175
- We didn't quite click. - Well, starting from yesterday...

2493
01:40:37,375 --> 01:40:39,814
Well, starting from yesterday,

2494
01:40:39,815 --> 01:40:42,845
he kept saying, "This is fun to do."

2495
01:40:43,285 --> 01:40:45,655
- Thank you, Hye Yoon. - I felt grateful for that.

2496
01:40:46,055 --> 01:40:48,125
It's a bummer that our time is so short.

2497
01:40:48,525 --> 01:40:50,384
By tomorrow, I could've snagged a star.

2498
01:40:50,385 --> 01:40:51,624
- I know. - Really?

2499
01:40:51,625 --> 01:40:52,694
Seriously.

2500
01:40:52,695 --> 01:40:54,895
(After a meal full of kind words)

2501
01:40:55,895 --> 01:40:58,635
(A moment later)

2502
01:40:59,665 --> 01:41:01,605
- Medium? - Medium, please.

2503
01:41:03,205 --> 01:41:04,234
My goodness.

2504
01:41:04,235 --> 01:41:05,404
(The five-star foot massage they've been waiting for)

2505
01:41:05,405 --> 01:41:07,105
We're in paradise.

2506
01:41:07,875 --> 01:41:10,074
Our eyes will be out of focus when we go down the steps.

2507
01:41:10,075 --> 01:41:11,415
I think so too.

2508
01:41:12,015 --> 01:41:14,885
Gosh, we were picking bananas not so long ago.

2509
01:41:16,045 --> 01:41:19,185
It's hard to believe that we were picking bananas.

2510
01:41:19,285 --> 01:41:20,285
Bananas...

2511
01:41:22,385 --> 01:41:25,854
(I was picking bananas.)

2512
01:41:25,855 --> 01:41:30,065
(Can I really enjoy such a luxury?)

2513
01:41:31,395 --> 01:41:33,394
We were thinking about using it on the first day,

2514
01:41:33,395 --> 01:41:34,665
but I'm glad that we kept it until the end.

2515
01:41:35,065 --> 01:41:37,164
Yes, we should relax before we leave.

2516
01:41:37,165 --> 01:41:38,175
You're right.

2517
01:41:38,275 --> 01:41:40,075
I couldn't have gotten it if you used it on the first day.

2518
01:41:40,535 --> 01:41:41,545
Exactly.

2519
01:41:42,645 --> 01:41:47,115
(A touch that soothes their feet tired from 5 days of hard work)

2520
01:41:48,645 --> 01:41:50,685
She's already asleep. My gosh.

2521
01:41:56,825 --> 01:41:59,224
Including her outfit, Jun Myun looks like a princess.

2522
01:41:59,225 --> 01:42:01,024
She's like Sleeping Beauty.

2523
01:42:01,025 --> 01:42:02,465
- What? - Gosh.

2524
01:42:02,665 --> 01:42:03,824
(The princess is...)

2525
01:42:03,825 --> 01:42:07,064
(not sleeping.)

2526
01:42:07,065 --> 01:42:09,465
- What? - Gosh, did you hear that?

2527
01:42:09,735 --> 01:42:11,205
My ears are wide open.

2528
01:42:11,635 --> 01:42:13,004
I didn't think...

2529
01:42:13,005 --> 01:42:14,005
(Unsleeping Beauty with open ears)

2530
01:42:14,375 --> 01:42:15,705
I've been waiting for this only.

2531
01:42:17,875 --> 01:42:21,385
In the morning, I picked bananas at a banana farm.

2532
01:42:23,415 --> 01:42:24,485
My feet...

2533
01:42:25,055 --> 01:42:26,254
(They lost their mind.)

2534
01:42:26,255 --> 01:42:27,685
They're very tired.

2535
01:42:28,625 --> 01:42:30,894
(The princess has been waiting for the massage only.)

2536
01:42:30,895 --> 01:42:33,155
Oh, yes. Come on.

2537
01:42:33,925 --> 01:42:35,464
Yes, good.

2538
01:42:35,465 --> 01:42:36,465
(Princess?)

2539
01:42:36,466 --> 01:42:38,795
Yes. Come on.

2540
01:42:42,835 --> 01:42:43,835
What?

2541
01:42:43,836 --> 01:42:45,205
(Her interjection shatters the peace.)

2542
01:42:45,505 --> 01:42:47,334
While dressed like a princess,

2543
01:42:47,335 --> 01:42:49,205
she says, "Yes, come on!"

2544
01:42:50,775 --> 01:42:52,275
Oh, good.

2545
01:42:54,145 --> 01:42:55,784
(30 minutes later,)

2546
01:42:55,785 --> 01:42:58,185
(everyone is in deep sleep.)

2547
01:43:00,455 --> 01:43:02,085
You only have 15 minutes left.

2548
01:43:03,225 --> 01:43:04,225
- What? - The massage?

2549
01:43:04,325 --> 01:43:05,924
- Only 15 minutes remain? - Oh, come on.

2550
01:43:05,925 --> 01:43:07,695
I only got a massage on one foot.

2551
01:43:08,395 --> 01:43:09,395
Ma'am?

2552
01:43:10,365 --> 01:43:11,995
The other leg, please.

2553
01:43:13,095 --> 01:43:15,205
- Change, please. - We don't have time.

2554
01:43:15,765 --> 01:43:17,304
- Change. - Change.

2555
01:43:17,305 --> 01:43:19,135
- Change. - Please hurry.

2556
01:43:19,375 --> 01:43:20,905
How do we say double speed in English?

2557
01:43:22,005 --> 01:43:24,344
(The dreamlike foot massage flies by...)

2558
01:43:24,345 --> 01:43:26,345
(as quickly as a dream.)

2559
01:43:27,845 --> 01:43:30,315
(The last sunset in Bohol is...)

2560
01:43:31,585 --> 01:43:34,255
(fading away.)

2561
01:43:35,425 --> 01:43:39,055
(Following the beautiful sunset)

2562
01:43:40,555 --> 01:43:43,394
(Obtained from harvesting coconuts on their third day)

2563
01:43:43,395 --> 01:43:44,435
My gosh.

2564
01:43:44,735 --> 01:43:46,364
(They arrive at the ocean view rooftop bar.)

2565
01:43:46,365 --> 01:43:49,035
I can't believe that we're seeing this on our last day.

2566
01:43:52,005 --> 01:43:53,675
Gosh, what's this?

2567
01:43:54,445 --> 01:43:55,445
(Exclaiming)

2568
01:43:56,645 --> 01:43:58,115
Look at that.

2569
01:43:59,745 --> 01:44:01,685
Isn't that parasailing?

2570
01:44:01,785 --> 01:44:03,845
- That looks fun. - Yes, that's it.

2571
01:44:04,885 --> 01:44:07,885
There are all the boats for island hopping.

2572
01:44:09,955 --> 01:44:13,325
Do people on each boat dance every day?

2573
01:44:14,525 --> 01:44:16,965
- What's that? - Didn't we get on the boat there?

2574
01:44:17,165 --> 01:44:18,165
Over there.

2575
01:44:21,135 --> 01:44:24,975
(Completely absorbed in taking selfies)

2576
01:44:27,575 --> 01:44:28,604
What are you doing?

2577
01:44:28,605 --> 01:44:29,605
(Letting out a laugh)

2578
01:44:29,945 --> 01:44:31,675
The background is beautiful.

2579
01:44:33,875 --> 01:44:35,545
She's laughing at what she said.

2580
01:44:35,715 --> 01:44:36,784
We have to take photos.

2581
01:44:36,785 --> 01:44:37,954
The light is in the back,

2582
01:44:37,955 --> 01:44:38,955
- so take it in this direction. - Right.

2583
01:44:39,385 --> 01:44:42,585
(If the light is in the back)

2584
01:44:43,755 --> 01:44:45,094
(They give up on the background.)

2585
01:44:45,095 --> 01:44:46,925
The view of the ocean is on the other side.

2586
01:44:48,395 --> 01:44:50,124
(We did come to an ocean view bar.)

2587
01:44:50,125 --> 01:44:51,935
(Featuring backlight)

2588
01:44:53,435 --> 01:44:55,705
The view is really beautiful.

2589
01:44:56,035 --> 01:44:57,774
It's stunning.

2590
01:44:57,775 --> 01:45:00,374
(Inside the unrealistically beautiful sunset in Bohol)

2591
01:45:00,375 --> 01:45:02,574
Shall we clink our glasses? Well done, everyone.

2592
01:45:02,575 --> 01:45:03,975
- Well done. - Well done.

2593
01:45:04,545 --> 01:45:06,275
(Guys, it was fun.)

2594
01:45:06,775 --> 01:45:07,785
It's so pretty.

2595
01:45:08,845 --> 01:45:09,985
She's taking another photo.

2596
01:45:10,615 --> 01:45:12,155
Isn't the color so pretty?

2597
01:45:12,255 --> 01:45:13,255
What is this?

2598
01:45:13,256 --> 01:45:14,925
(The youngest princess takes a photo with her cocktail.)

2599
01:45:15,725 --> 01:45:18,354
(The second eldest princess starts drinking immediately.)

2600
01:45:18,355 --> 01:45:19,425
Gosh.

2601
01:45:19,995 --> 01:45:21,764
People can be so fickle.

2602
01:45:21,765 --> 01:45:24,665
I was exhausted from picking bananas until this afternoon.

2603
01:45:24,895 --> 01:45:26,564
But after a massage, I felt totally relaxed.

2604
01:45:26,565 --> 01:45:28,564
- I felt so much better. - Exactly.

2605
01:45:28,565 --> 01:45:30,365
After a massage, I wanted to stay here one more day.

2606
01:45:31,205 --> 01:45:35,075
How about a full-body massage tomorrow?

2607
01:45:35,305 --> 01:45:36,675
I stayed here only two nights.

2608
01:45:36,775 --> 01:45:38,274
- Yes, I know. - Wasn't it too short?

2609
01:45:38,275 --> 01:45:39,344
My stay was too short.

2610
01:45:39,345 --> 01:45:40,345
(Disappointed by such a short trip)

2611
01:45:40,346 --> 01:45:43,284
Five days flew by.

2612
01:45:43,285 --> 01:45:45,115
- Don't you think? - Right.

2613
01:45:45,455 --> 01:45:46,784
Playing in the water was so much fun.

2614
01:45:46,785 --> 01:45:48,325
I had so much fun.

2615
01:45:48,425 --> 01:45:49,484
I had fun thanks to you.

2616
01:45:49,485 --> 01:45:50,925
Really? Thank you.

2617
01:45:51,795 --> 01:45:53,855
What I realized once again is...

2618
01:45:53,955 --> 01:45:55,325
that Hye Yoon is fearless.

2619
01:45:56,095 --> 01:45:58,064
Hye Yoon isn't your average girl.

2620
01:45:58,065 --> 01:45:59,065
(She proved that she wasn't ordinary.)

2621
01:45:59,066 --> 01:46:01,505
We asked him once on "Adventure by Accident."

2622
01:46:02,235 --> 01:46:04,535
"Who do you like better, us or these sisters?"

2623
01:46:05,405 --> 01:46:08,045
He said that he liked the sisters better.

2624
01:46:08,345 --> 01:46:10,205
He prefers the sisters on Fresh Off the Sea.

2625
01:46:10,905 --> 01:46:11,915
(Blowing her nose)

2626
01:46:13,245 --> 01:46:15,014
- Jun Myun. - He's saying something nice.

2627
01:46:15,015 --> 01:46:16,015
Come on, Jun Myun.

2628
01:46:16,016 --> 01:46:17,144
I'm saying something really nice.

2629
01:46:17,145 --> 01:46:19,814
Don't wipe your eyes with what you used to wipe your nose.

2630
01:46:19,815 --> 01:46:21,384
You're driving me crazy.

2631
01:46:21,385 --> 01:46:22,385
Why would you go crazy?

2632
01:46:22,386 --> 01:46:24,384
- Hey. - I care about Jun Myun.

2633
01:46:24,385 --> 01:46:27,894
Both of you worked so hard without showing a hint of struggle.

2634
01:46:27,895 --> 01:46:29,465
No, we didn't.

2635
01:46:30,325 --> 01:46:32,064
When we leave, I'll miss you guys for a few days.

2636
01:46:32,065 --> 01:46:33,135
We spent every day together.

2637
01:46:34,505 --> 01:46:38,074
A group like this spent five days together...

2638
01:46:38,075 --> 01:46:41,805
while laughing, joking, and never having a single argument.

2639
01:46:42,245 --> 01:46:45,015
It's amazing that we were together all the time.

2640
01:46:45,645 --> 01:46:49,085
I feel like I got to travel with such wonderful people.

2641
01:46:49,585 --> 01:46:50,915
I will miss them very much.

2642
01:46:51,655 --> 01:46:54,115
Fresh Off the Sea was a lot of fun.

2643
01:46:54,578 --> 01:46:57,988
(A bonus scene is coming up.)

2644
01:46:58,231 --> 01:46:59,361
(The siblings get ready to leave.)

2645
01:46:59,531 --> 01:47:00,791
Mark.

2646
01:47:01,271 --> 01:47:02,570
(Assigned Marker who took care of them for 4 nights and 5 days)

2647
01:47:02,571 --> 01:47:03,631
Hey.

2648
01:47:04,601 --> 01:47:06,170
- Mark. - Mark.

2649
01:47:06,171 --> 01:47:07,601
Goodbye.

2650
01:47:07,701 --> 01:47:08,840
Thank you.

2651
01:47:08,841 --> 01:47:10,340
(Mark and the siblings got attached in a short time.)

2652
01:47:10,341 --> 01:47:11,981
You've worked so hard.

2653
01:47:12,181 --> 01:47:13,810
(Saying goodbye to each of them)

2654
01:47:13,811 --> 01:47:16,651
Mark did such a great job. He was so friendly.

2655
01:47:17,351 --> 01:47:18,351
Take care.

2656
01:47:18,352 --> 01:47:21,251
(He hugs Dex, whom he was close.)

2657
01:47:21,591 --> 01:47:23,451
Which one do you prefer? Try them on.

2658
01:47:24,091 --> 01:47:26,291
Yes, pick a pair that you like.

2659
01:47:26,421 --> 01:47:28,691
I bet he'll like the first ones better.

2660
01:47:29,561 --> 01:47:31,560
These, right? Are they your type?

2661
01:47:31,561 --> 01:47:33,001
These are for you, okay?

2662
01:47:33,101 --> 01:47:34,531
These are for your wife.

2663
01:47:34,701 --> 01:47:35,900
Really?

2664
01:47:35,901 --> 01:47:37,871
(Showing gratitude to Mark with a small present)

2665
01:47:37,941 --> 01:47:40,000
Take photos with me, okay?

2666
01:47:40,001 --> 01:47:41,840
Okay. Promise me.

2667
01:47:41,841 --> 01:47:42,841
I promise.
(They promised each other for the last photo shoot.)

2668
01:47:43,841 --> 01:47:44,841
Mark, stand in the center.

2669
01:47:45,411 --> 01:47:47,081
(As promised, he gets ready to take the photo.)

2670
01:47:48,581 --> 01:47:49,880
I'm not crying.

2671
01:47:49,881 --> 01:47:51,720
Don't cry.

2672
01:47:51,721 --> 01:47:52,920
Oh, my gosh.

2673
01:47:52,921 --> 01:47:54,950
- What? - Don't cry.

2674
01:47:54,951 --> 01:47:56,120
Don't cry, baby.

2675
01:47:56,121 --> 01:47:58,691
(Mark's tears make the siblings also cry.)

2676
01:48:00,991 --> 01:48:02,490
(On their first Fresh Off the Sea abroad,)

2677
01:48:02,491 --> 01:48:05,431
(they make new friends and cherished memories.)

2678
01:48:05,831 --> 01:48:07,900
(Yum Jung Ah, Park Jun Myun)

2679
01:48:07,901 --> 01:48:10,231
(Dex, Kim Hye Yoon)

2680
01:48:10,831 --> 01:48:13,101
(Thank you for watching Fresh Off the Sea in Calape.)

2681
01:48:13,501 --> 01:48:17,011
(We will be back again.)
